reviewText: Wrestlemania XIX was a solid ppv, but as a Wrestlemania it was sub par. Wrestlemania has to have something that distinguishes itself from all other ppvs and while Wrestlemania XIX didn't have a bad match on the card there was nothing really spectacular about them either.Matt Hardy w/Shannon Moore vs. Rey Mysterio for the Cruiserweight Championship-A solid opener and kudos to the WWE for not going with the obvious outcome. However,as much as I like Matt Hardy this match seemed to just delay the inevitable outcome of Rey beating Matt and allowed them to drag out their feud for the next few months. Rey winning at Wrestlemania would have made this a better match, but whatever. A solid match in itself I give it 7 out of 10 stars.Undertaker vs. The Big Show and A-Train-This was originaly supposed to be a tag team match with Nathan Jones, but mercifully he was set up by the FBI(E-C-Dub,well sort of) and taken out by the Big Show and A-Train. Being that his is Wrestlemania the Undertaker puts on another solid match. Nothing Special, but still a very good match. I give this one 7 out of 10 as well.Victoria w/Steven Richards vs Trish Stratus vs.Jazz for the Women's Championship-I'm not a big fan of women's wrestling matches. They're entertaining, but as a wrestling fan I sometimes cringe as to how much time they are given. With that said this was at least entertaining. Trish is a decent wrestler and Victoria isn't bad either. I've never been a big Jazz fan, but that's a different story. Good to see Steven Richards on Wrestlemania. Overall, 5 out of 10.Team Angle vs. Los Guerreros vs. Chris Benoit and Rhyno in a Triple Threat for the WWE Tag Team Championships. Los Guerreros rule. Team Angle(now The World's Greatest Tag Team) rule and Benoit and Rhyno rule. Benoit, Rhyno, and Eddie Guerrero make their return to Wrestlemania(all three last appeared at Wrestlemania X7) and Chavo Guerrero and Team Angle make their Wrestlemania debut. This was a great tag team match. Good to see one of the programs still putting on good tag team matches(I miss the days of Edge/Christian,the Hardyz,and the Dudleyz). The match was fast paced and it's good to see the "rookies" come away with the belts. I give it an 8 out of 10.Shawn Michaels vs Chris Jericho-People aren't exagerating when they say this was the match of the night. Shawn Michaels might not be what he used to be, but he's still better than a lot of the wrestlers out there and Chris jericho is really is good as he says he is. Doubt me? Check out some of his older matches to see what he can really do. I'm not talking about WCW matches either i'm talking about Benoit/Jericho in Japan circa 1995. Anyways, a good feud that started right after Armageddon in December and continued on through the Royal Rumble and No Way Out. Shawn Michaels showed that he could still "hang with the younger guys" and that the Showstopper lived. I give it a 10 out of 10.Booker T vs. Triple H for the World Heavyweight Championship-Finally,the Five Time WCW Champion gets a shot at a belt he should have already won at least once. Both wrestlers pulled out all stops in a feud that seemed to come together too quickly. It is only the ending that keeps this match from being a 10 star match. As it is it's 8 out of 10.Hulk Hogan vs Vince McMahon the Street Fight 20 Years in the Making-Hogan's done a lot to make wrestling mainstream. However,he's not know for having technically sound matches. But this is Vince McMahon and all wrestling skills do not apply. This is a very entertaining match from top to bottom and it does have that only-at-Wrestlemania mystique. Vince pulled out all stops including a leg drop off a ladder onto Hogan who was laying on the spanish announce table and bringing back Rowdy Roddy Piper. However,none of it mattered as Hogan still came out on top. Like I said don't watch this match for the wrestling watch it for the entertainment value. 8 out of 10.Stone Cold Steve Austin vs The Rock Part 3-The Rock is the man. Love him or hate him The Rock is one of the few guys who can go away from wrestling and still come back at the top of his game better than he was before he left. The Rock and Austin always put on good matches at Wrestlemania and with this being the "Final Chapter" of their feud i'd expect no less. While this is not as good as their previous encounter at Wrestlemania X7 it is still an awesome match. Finally, The Rock gets what he should have gotten at Wrestlemania X7 and that's a victory over Austin. 8 out of 10.Brock Lesnar vs Kurt Angle for the WWE Championship-Like Angle/Benoit this is a purist's dream and a match that the WWE has been building up to since Lesnar came to the WWE. Unfortunately,Angle suffered a nearly career ending neck injury shortly before the ppv which seemingly put the match in jeopardy. During the match however their were no signs of injury by Angle as he and Lesnar put on one hell of a wrestling clinic. On any other ppv this would have been the match of the night, but this is Wrestlemania and for some reason, at least to me, this match lacked something. Maybe knowing that Angle would be leaving right afterwards to have surgery took something away from the outcome or perhaps it was the botched shooting star press by Lesnar, a move that would have distinguished the match. Overall,though a high impact wrestling match that was technically sound. 8 out of 10.Like I said Wrestlemania XIX is a good ppv, but as a Wrestlemania it lacks something. The dvd itself is awesome with lots of extras including Goldberg's debut the following night on RAW and lots of promotional spots and Wrestlemania flashbacks. If you're a WWE fan you should buy the dvd anyways, so go ahead and do it.

reviewText: A few people below me are way too hyper about this DVD.  WMXIX was way better than WMX8, but not even close to being better than WM17.  Here are the matches:WWE Cruiserweight Title: Matt Hardy vs. Rey Mysterio.  Way too short.  The match was only 5 minutes long.  Their match on Smackdown! where Rey won the title was much better.  **Undertaker vs. Big SHow and A-Train.  Pretty slow, but still ok.  Nathan was attacked before so it became a handicap match, but later Nathan helps Taker out to make his streak at WM 11-0. **1/2Women's Title: Victoria vs. Trish vs. Jazz.  Honestly probably the best women's title match I've seen, and I don't care about those matches much.  Trish wins, how shocking is that, pff. ***WWE SD tag Titles: Los Guerreros vs. Team Angle vs. Benoit and Rhyno.  This could of been a match to steal the show, if given about 40 minutes, but this match only lasted 10, and was completely boring because of such a short amount of time.  **HBK vs. Jericho.  Now we're talking.  Their fued had lasted about 4 months, and finally it was to end at WMXIX, and what a match these two put on.  This match was the one that stole the show(either it or Hogan vs. McMahon).  These two stole each others' moves and finishers, and in the end, HBK won with a roll-up.  *****World Title: Triple H vs. Booker T.  This match could of been much better, but it was ok.  I should of known Triple H would win since he always wins when it comes to the title basically.  Triple H beat Booker T fair i believe...scary.  ***Street Fight: Hogan vs. McMahon.  I thought this match would be a total disaster, and it really bugged me that this was the most talked about match before WMXIX happened, but this match was great.  It was bloody, plenty of punishment, and McMahon even did a leg drop off the ladder onto Hogan thru the announce table.  Rowdy Roddy Piper even made a shocking appearance.  But a great match, and a bloody hogan won.  *****Stone Cold vs. Rock.  IMO, better than their WM15 match, but not better than their match at WM17.  Their fued from WM17 was always intense, but theirs for WMXIX was more about mindgames from Rock and Austin. Still a great match tho, and Rock wins.  ***1/2WWE Title: Kurt Angle vs. Brock Lesner.  I didn't really think this match would be too good, especially with Kurt having neck problems, but it was great.  It definately deserved to be the main event.  These two gave it their all in this match, even Brock going for a shooting star press(which brock didn't nail all the way and it gave him a concussion).  Brock wins the WWE Title after 3 F-5s on Kurt Angle.  ****The extras are not as good as I had hoped, but are still ok.  Are they worth buying for DVD?  I dunno, there are only like 2 extras I like on here, and that's Goldberg's Debut and WWE talking about Taker's undefeated streak.  But WMXIX is pretty good, but if ya want one of the best(if not the best) WM's to watch, get WM17.  It wont disappoint.
summary: Pretty good, but not the best...

reviewText: 1. Cruiserweight Title Match: Rey Mysterio vs. Matt Hardy (c)Decent match I suppose, but not really too much here. It consists of a couple interesting spots, coupled with much interference from Shannon Moore, Matt Hardy's "manager" of sorts. I preferred Matt Hardy when he was with Jeff, but he isn't a bad wrestler on his own. Decent opener, worth a look. 5/102. Handicap Match: Big Show and A-Train vs. The UndertakerThe Undertaker does all he can in this one. Yet another mediocre 'Mania match for the Deadman, which is a shame considering how talented he is. Rather boring, though its worth watching to see Taker continune his streak. 5/103. Women's Championship Match: Victoria vs. Jazz vs. Trish StratusStandard women's match, actually better then I expected. Skip this though, not worth a watch. 4/104. WWE Tag Team Championship Match: Los Guerreros vs. Chris Benoit and Rhyno vs. Team AngleGood tag match that shows the athleticism and in-ring talent of all the men involved. Definitely worth a look, first good match of the night. 6/105. Chris Jericho vs. Shawn MichaelsAs a big HBK fan, I was really looking forward to seeing this match. Again, Shawn proves why he is deserving of the nickname "Mr. Wrestlemania", as he puts on another amazing performance with Chris Jericho, possibly one of the most underrated wrestlers of his time. Jericho is a great wrestler that doesn't get enough credit. These two work exceptionally well here, and this is without a doubt one of the greatest Wrestlemania matches of all time. An epic contest, don't miss this. 9.5/106. Cat Fight: Miller Light Cat Fight Girls vs. Stacy Keibler and Torrie WilsonWatch for the women. Dissapointing that Coach shows up, but its still nice to see Stacy and Torrie. 4/10 (for Stacy)7. World Heavyweight Championship Match: Booker T vs. Triple H (c)Average world title match, though its a bit of a random match-up. Not bad, but nothing special either. 6.5/108. Street Fight: Vince McMahon vs. Hulk HoganVery hyped match, and I don't think it delivered. One good spot in the whole match, and has some entertaining moments, but the first 10 or so minutes is extremely boring. The ending gets exciting, from the ladder spot (you'll know what I mean) on. A rather random run-in too, but overall its worth a watch. 6.5/109. Stone Cold Steve Austin vs. The RockNot as good as their previous two encounters, at Wrestlemania XV and X-7. Still a great match though, these two work very well in the ring. It's very back and forth and exciting throughout the entire match. I think its a great way to end Stone Cold's career, considering even though he was in the hospital the night before, he puts on an excellent performance. Great job by both men, definitely worth a watch. 8.5/1010. WWE Championship Match: Brock Lesnar vs. Kurt Angle (c)One word for this match: overrated. Definitely a good match, but I think its excellence is greatly exaggerated. It has the feel and the hype of a main event at Wrestlemania, and they deliver, but its not as good as people praise it. The now-famous Shooting Star Press that Lesnar attempts is a must see. Overall, this is a good Wrestlemania Main Event, but is generally overrated. 8/10Overall, this is a pretty good Wrestlemania that delivers in most areas. Nothing horrible on this card, but certainly a few mediocre matches, as well as poor use of some excellent wrestlers.Match of the Night: Jericho vs. Michaels, by far. Probable "match of the year" winner. Amazing, amazing match.

reviewText: WM XIX was truly a great PPV, it featured some of the greatest matches ever seen. Here are some of the more notable bouts:WWE Championship MatchKurt Angle(c) vs. Brock Lesnar*****-A spectacular match and possibly the greatest WM main-event ever. The WWE Title Match is on par with HBK/Jericho, even though Angle came in with a broken neck and some questioned if he would be 100%. Brock suffered a concussion too, after a botched Shooting Star Press, but amazingly, he was still able to deliver the F-5 to win the WWE Championship."Stone Cold" Steve Austin vs. The Rock*****-These two delivered one amazing match! Then again, who expected anything less? Austin and Rock had a tremendous battle that may have not been on the same page as their WM X-7 clash but it was still a great and full with false finishes and out of the ring brawling. This match will be historical as well because it may be Austin's last match.Street Fight "20 Years in the Making":Hulk Hogan vs. Mr. McMahon****1/2-Imagine that, two 50-year olds actually had a better match than Triple H and Booker T. Nobody expected much from this match but they were proven wrong when McMahon and Hogan tore the house down! Vince even brought out a ladder! Not to mention a suprise run-in from Roddy Piper!World Heavyweight Championship MatchTriple H(c) vs. Booker T****-A pretty good match, certainly not as good as it could have been but good none the less. There was even some mat wrestling supplied by "The Game" that is rarely seen nowadays. Kudos to Booker T who delivered an awesome Houston Hangtime. The finish was a little weak though.Shawn Michaels vs. Chris Jericho*****-Tied with Brock/Angle as best match of the night, spectators expected this match to steal the show and did it ever! 20 minutes of great wrestling, both countered hold-for-hold and this is HBK's best match in a while.Plus:Triple-Threat WWE Tag Team Championship MatchCharlie Haas(c) & Shelton Benjamin(c) vs Eddie Guerrero & Chavo Guerrero vs Chris Benoit & RhynoTriple-Threat Women Championship MatchVictoria(c) with Steven Richards vs. Trish Stratus vs. JazzUndertaker vs. Big Show & A-TrainWWE Cruiserweight Championship MatchMatt Hardy(c) with Shannon Moore vs. Rey Mysterio...and plenty of DVD extras!

reviewText: WWE Cruiserweight ChampionshipMatt Hardy vs. Rey MysterioGreat to see this title at the biggest show.  What a great match! Perfect opener.  Don't blink.Undertaker vs. Big Show & A-TrainNot bad.  A little slow but Taker actually carries both men.  Made exciting by Taker's streak.Triple Threat Match for the Women's ChampionshipVictoria vs. Jazz vs. Trish StratusThis has to be the best women's match of all time.  A surprisingly fluent match with great moves and genuine excitement.WWE Tag Team ChampionshipTeam Angle vs. Los Guerreros vs. Chris Benoit & RhynoAnother great match!  5 of the 6 competitors in this match are world class pro wrestlers and they prove it in this one.Shawn Michaels vs. Chris JerichoA dream match!  An absolute classic and a fitting return to WM for HBK.  One of the best matches of all time.World Heavyweight ChampionshipTriple H vs. Booker TFinally the Bookerman gets his due.  A very good match that saw both men break out some moves that had been stowed away for a long time.Street Fight 20 Years in the MakingHulk Hogan vs. Vince McMahonYou have to give it up to both men.  Their age & real life feud could've made this terrible but no way.  Superlative effort from both men.  The video package before this is one of the best ever. A lot of real emotion in this match and you could see it on their faces.  A classic.WWE ChampionshipKurt Angle vs. Brock LesnarPredictable but wow!  A top 5 WM main event. reviewText: I would rate Wrestlemania XIX as arguably the best Wrestlemania ever.  The WWE Superstars gave everything they had in every match - especially in the triple-threat women's title match - and overall fan enthusiasm at the SAFECO field arena in Seattle, Washington was very high.  Other noteworthy matches were the Hogan-McMahon streetfight, Angle vs. Lesnar, and The Rock vs. Austin (I was glad to see "the People's Champion" - with three devasting Rock Bottom slams - finally score a Wrestlemania pinfall win over "the Rattlesnake").There are two reasons, however, why I'm only giving Wrestlemania XIX a four- as opposed to a five-star rating:  1) the four-woman "catfight" was a little silly (plus, I didn't need to see the Coach in his Fruit-o'-the-Looms), though I'm sure others enjoyed it; and 2) I really felt that Booker T should've won the World Heavyweight Title from Triple H.  "The Game," the great althelete that he is, has held that belt far too long; meanwhile, Booker T has seriously paid his dues since coming to the WWE in 2001 and, in my opinion, REALLY deserved it, as well as a win at "the Granddaddy of 'em all."  I sincerely hope that this isn't a bad omen of things to come as far as Booker T's major title prospects in the WWE are concerned.Overall, Vince McMahon outdid himself this year.
summary: Arguably The Best Ever - but with a couple of drawbacks.

reviewText: <50: Ask for a refund for not only your money, but also your time. [F]50-54: Mediocre & disappointing. [D] (EG: UnForgiven 2002)55-59: Average. [C]60-64: Worth A Watch. [C+] (EG: No Mercy 2002, Armageddon 2002 & No Way Out 2003)65-69: Good event that was worth the money. [B] (EG: Survivor Series 2002 & Royal Rumble 2003)70-74: Very good. [B+]75-79: Make sure you add this ppv to your video or dvd collection. [A] (EG: SummerSlam 2002)80+ : Make sure that the video or dvd is locked in a safe & cannot be erased. Memorable. [A+]MATT HARDY defeated REY MYSTERIO to Retain the CruiserWeight Title: I only wanted 2 things out of this match. I thought if it had those 2 factors, the rest would take care of itself. Firstly, that it was the first bout on the card. I have long been an advocate of cruiserweight matches opening up any show to get the crowd hot. This was also done well on the SmackDown before WrestleMania. Secondly, I wanted it to last at least 12 minutes. Not 20, not even 15, just 12. I got 6 measly minutes. The match was still good, but it didn't really allow the duo to show how truly talented they are. Match Rating...7THE UNDERTAKER defeated THE BIG SHOW & A-TRAIN: What can I say about the WWE deciding to leave my fellow countryman Nathan Jones out of this match. It was a good decision as he is not ready for an event as big as WrestleMania, and he probably wouldn't have got a great deal of help from his colleagues in the ring. The Undertaker impressed me for the second pay-per-view in a row, and I'm starting to think that the time off he had has done him the world of good. This was far from a classic, but it was sufficiently entertaining & had a decent finish that made sense. Match Rating...6TRISH STRATUS defeated VICTORIA & JAZZ to Win the Women's Title: A very good match. This was a fitting climax to the seemingly never-ending feud between these three ladies. The bout was well planned & structured, while it also was void of any major botched moves which has plagued the division for quite some time now. Now if only the division can add a little more depth to cover the loss of Victoria while she has knee surgery. Match Rating...7SHELTON BENJAMIN/CHARLIE HAAS defeated LOS GUERREROS & RHYNO/CHRIS BENOIT to Retain the WWE Tag-Team Championship: This was another good match that could have been a fair bit better if it was given more time to play out. Team Angle acquitted themselves quite well on the big stage, but the real surprise for me here was Chavo Guerrero. I have thought for quite some time that Chavo is not up to the better wrestlers in the WWE, and while that still holds true, I thought he played a major role in the better parts of this match. Hopefully, he can use this match as a kick-start to his career. Match Rating...7SHAWN MICHAELS defeated CHRIS JERICHO: Many people, including myself, believed that this would be the match of the night. It did not disappoint, and was enthralling for most of it's 20+ minutes. The result was very debatable though. And I'm not saying that because it was the only match on the card that I incorrectly predicted. Also debatable is whether or not Chris Jericho will get his long-deserved push from this match. While it was the match of the night, it lacked that classic attention-grabbing characteristics that those type of matches often have. However, in isolation, this was an extremely entertaining & satisfying bout between 2 top-notch performers. Match Rating...9TRIPLE H defeated BOOKER T to Retain the World HeavyWeight Title: This match was disappointing in my mind. I was really expecting the two to fit in quite well with each other & I was quietly confident of a very good match. But the glove just didn't fit, so to speak. Booker T looked reluctant to push his offense, while Triple H unfortunately did not step up as I thought he might (because it was WrestleMania). It's a shame, as I was really hoping for a rematch at Backlash where Booker would win the title. Now I'm not so sure. This was far from terrible, but it wasn't great. Match Rating...6HULK HOGAN defeated VINCE McMAHON: I really can't add too much about this match that you probably didn't think yourself. Apart from the strange & unexpected Rowdy Roddy Piper appearance, this was a predictable & entertaining 20 minute streetfight which saw lots of blood spilt. In a way I'm glad this wasn't the main event of the evening, as I thought it was a poor man's version of the WrestleMania 17 match between Vince & Shane McMahon. But like I said, it was entertaining. Especially the "Here's Vince" mat-high camera shot of a bloodied Vince peeking over the apron with that prototypical maniacal look of his. Match Rating...7THE ROCK defeated STONE COLD STEVE AUSTIN: Definitely not up to the standard of their two previous WrestleMania matches, this bout just seemed to be missing something. It was probably because neither man (especially Austin) is at the top of their game right now. It was still entertaining though, in a similar way to the previous (Hogan/McMahon) match. The ending was a little strange, as it took 3 Rock Bottoms to put away Austin. But at the end of the day, the correct person won, in my opinion. Match Rating...7BROCK LESNAR defeated KURT ANGLE to Win the WWE Championship: Firstly, I'm glad that the WWE decided to have this as their main event of the evening. The match started off scratchily, but gathered momentum rather nicely as it went along. This was probably more to do with the settling of nerves for both competitors. Angle's neck injury was only really noticeable if you looked for it. I tried not to, so as to attempt to judge the match on it's merits. The ending finally came & I just knew that Lesnar was finally going to drag out his shooting star press. It just made sense to do so. But as he looked at the top rope, I immediately realized that Angle would be too far away. I was expecting Angle to crawl to the middle of the ring. What Lesnar attempted was extremely ambitious (if still very impressive) to say the least. The two did well to continue the match afterwards, and overall, this was an above average match which was a sufficient WrestleMania main event. Match Rating...8PPV RATING (64/90) = 71Looking at the key, I have basically given WrestleMania 19 a 'B+' grade & said that it was 'very good'. I'm happy with that overall grade & comment. The event was very even from top to bottom. Probably trailing only WrestleMania 14 as the most even WrestleMania of all time. All matches received pass grades & were definitely watchable. While the Michaels vs Jericho match was excellent, it probably failed to live up to the 'match of the nights' from previous WrestleManias. Predictability also hurt this event a little, as nothing really shocking happened. Hell, if I had to pick one thing that genuinely astounded me from the night, it would probably be Brock Lesnar's botched shooting star press. Overall though, a very entertaining watch. The WWE have delivered on pay-per-view once more.

reviewText: Wrestlemania waxes nostalgic, as Vince gives a bow to "old school" style wrestling. Here are my ratings of the matches based out of 5 *****:WWE Cruiserweight Championship Matt Hardy vs Rey Mysterio - Non-stop high-flying moves abound.  Great aeriel action. Wine me, dine me, 6 1 9 me.  Ray gives his all, but is it enough? Nice match to start the show.  Rating - ****Limp Bizkit comes out and plays "Rollin'" live - "Limp" is right!The Undertaker rides out on a motorcycle with a big American flag trailing the bike (YAWN). The crowd cheers louder for The Undertaker than Limp Bizkit, LOL! Or are they cheering because Bizkit is leaving?Undertaker & Nathan Jones vs Big Show & A-Train - Nathan Jones gets jumped in the locker-room before the match, and the Undertaker has to square off against Big Show and A-Train alone! This is a fantastic big man match, with some great technical wrestling and submission holds.  The action is non-stop and the Undertaker shows his wrestling prowess. The best big man match I have ever seen. Does The Undertaker have enough to beat the Big Show AND A-Train by himself? I doubt it! Great match. Rating - *****Trple-Threat Woman's Championship Match - Champion Victoria vs Trish Stratus vs Jazz -  A GREAT match!  Alot of great moves and wrestling. This is just a awesome wrestling match.  I was surprised at how well this went.  Rating - *****Triple-Threat Tag Team Championship - Champions Charlie Hass/Shelton Benjamin vs Eddie Guerrero/Chavo Guerrero vs Chris Benoit/Rhyno -  Fantastic match with great tag team action.  The hitting is nonstop, and the moves are powerful. Everyone gets ring time. Just another awesome match. Rating - *****Shawn Michaels vs Chris Jericho -  The match of night as far as I'm concerned (and that's saying something because this is one HELL of a card)! The crowd is really pumped and pulling for HBK. A great, long match that highlights each wrestler's abilities and moves.  All of the moves are brought out: technical, submission, aeriel, as well as ring psychology. A very intense and athletic match. Who's finisher reigns supreme? Awesome Baby! Rating - *****Limp Bizkit plays another live number, "Crack Addict" and dampens the crowds enthusiasm with their "Limp" "music".Heavyweight Championship Match - Champion Triple H vs Booker T - A good match with alot of power bombs and hard hitting. Triple H breaks out a new submission/finisher.  Is it enough to beat the 5-time world champion Booker T? A good match that would score higher if there weren't so many rest breaks. Rating - ****Street Fight - Hulk Hogan vs Mr. McMahon - No wrestling just pure pummeling!  The blood flows like a river.  Everything and anything is used to beat, cut, pound, cripple the other.  Most of the fight is outside of the ring, and ANYONE in their way gets pulverized.  Look out announcers!  Pure EXTREME style. Rating - ****Stone Cold Steve Austin vs The Rock - This is Stone Cold's final match and the Rock tries to make it Austin's final day on earth! This match picks right up were Hulk and McMahon left off - outside of the ring, pounding each other into submission! Thie crowd is way into the match and really pulling for Stone Cold. The Rock does his best imitation of Austin. Damn, can The Rock entertain a crowd!  How many "Rock Bottoms" does it take to open a "Can of Whoop Ass"? Watch and see! He's the best, and that's the "Stone Cold Truth"! Rating - *****WWE Championship Match - Champion Kurt Angle vs Brock Lesnar - Two of the best wrestlers in the world go toe to toe!  How can this NOT be a 5 star match.  Alot of chain-wrestling and amature/technical holds and moves.  Submission moves and high-impact power slams.  What can I say other than Frickin' AWESOME! Rating - *****Overall, this is the BEST Wrestlemania I have seen so far. Vice finally introduces wrestling to his Wrestlemania show and it pays off big time!  If you like WRESTLING, this is the one to see!  Get it while you still can!  Highly recommended!

reviewText: I hadn't seen the extras but I can comment on the card itself as I have seen it:WWE Championship match: Kurt Angle vs. Brock Lesnar - Two former amature wrestlers fighting for the WWE Title. That's very rare. One uses strength and technique to win (Angle) while the other is brute power with technical skills (Lesner). Very good match with a shocking and, quite frankly, scary ending!Stone Cold Steve Austin vs. The Rock - Not a bad match but definitely not as good as their first two WM encounters! The Rock, surprisingly, used more wrestling than he has in the past Vs. Austin at WM. Usually, they were all out brawls but this time Rocky used great psychology. Austin, while in great looking shape, isn't what he was even a year ago. Still, a good match.Street Fight "20 Years in the Making": Hulk Hogan vs. Mr. McMahon - Surprisingly well done! Very entertaining match!World Heavyweight Championship Match: Triple H vs. Booker T - I have not really brought myself to watch this whole match yet for personal reason. Suffice to say HHH should've lost!Shawn Michaels vs. Chris Jericho - The best match at WM 19 without question! A classic WM match!Triple-Threat WWE Tag Team Championship Match: Charlie Haas and Shelton Benjamin vs. Eddie Guerrero and Chavo Guerrero vs. Chris Benoit and Rhyno - Decent bout but could've been better.Triple-Threat Women's Championship Match: Victoria with Steven Richards vs. Trish Stratus vs. Jazz - Surprisingly good. Jazz was great as always as was Victoria. Trish isn't that good of a wrestler though she is certainly better than she was 2 years ago. Hot outfit she wore for the match though! Got to give Trish that!Undertaker & Nathan Jones vs. Big Show & A-Train - This was basically a two on one match. The best thing about this match was that they went back to "Rollin'" by Limp Bizkit for this one! HALLELUAH THERE IS A GOD!WWE Cruiserweight Championship Match: Matt Hardy with Shannon Moore vs. Rey Mysterio - Good match up but WAAAAY too short!

reviewText: This was an incredible wrestling event. I saw it live on PPV this year and it was awesome! I bought it on DVD when it came out in June. I'm happy to write a review on this DVD. If you're a true wrestling fan, then you should really like this DVD. It has a lot of extras and highlights. Wrestlemania 19 delivers some pretty good wrestling action. Here's a listing of the matches from the event (each one with a star rating):Cruiserweight ChampionshipMatt Hardy vs. Rey Mysterio **1/2This match was good, except it was way too short!  Still, a great way to start out Wrestlemania. The crowd really got into it.A-Train & Bigshow vs. The Undertaker **The Undertaker deserved to be placed in a better matchup than this. The match didn't stink. But it didn't make me cheer much either. The ending was cool, with Nathan Jones delivering a big boot to the Bigshow and Undertaker tombstoning A-Train for the win.World Heavyweight ChampionshipBooker T vs. Triple H ***1/2 BR> HHH can be a pretty boring wrestler. And he's been the WWE World Heavyweight Champion long enough. But this time, Triple H actually had a decent match. While not really a classic, Booker T and HHH did manage to put on one heck of a technical wrestling match, and perhaps one of the best matches of the entire PPV. Sadly, Booker T doesn't win the championship, but the match was a lot better than I'd given it credit for.Women's ChampionshipTrish Stratus vs. Victoria vs. Jazz *** The best women's match I've seen in a while! And the hottest babe won! I sure miss Lita.WWE Tag Team ChampionshipTeam Angle vs. Rhyno & Chris Benoit vs. Los Gurreros **1/4  This match could've been a lot better. It wasn't long enough and the ending was a bit disappointing. Overall, it was still fairly good.Chris Jericho vs. "HBK" Shawn Michaels *****This was definetly Wrestlemania quality & easily the best match of the night. Shawn Michaels & Chris Jericho stole the show and gave a perfect example of what true technical wrestling is all about!!!"Stone Cold" Steve Austin vs. The Rock ****Although their match at Wrestlemania 17 was much better, this match still deserves a whole lot of credit & admiration. There was no interference in this match, and we actually got to see who the better man was. This match wasn't nearly as brutal & violent as some of their past wars, but it did live up to its hype. And while Austin couldn't quite beat The Rock this time, it did take 3 rockbottoms just to put him away! Very good match."Streetfight" w/ Hogan's career on the line.Vince McMahon vs. Hulk Hogan ****  Going into this match, I didn't know what to expect. There was a ton of hype going into it. As it turned out, it was everything I wanted it to be: bloody, brutal, and highly entertaining. The part where Mr. McMahon legdrops Hogan through the announce table from a ladder was off the page. The match had one heck of a climax.WWE ChampionshipBrock Lesnar vs. Kurt Angle ****1/2Both men gave everything they had to put on one heck of a matchup. It only dragged on a little bit at a couple of spots, but it still turned out to be one awesome match. It had a terrific flow to it. Great sportsmanship, great athletisicm, and brilliant courage by Kurt Angle (who was suffering from neck trauma) made this match what it was. Kurt Angle was even able to kick out of an F-5. Brock Lesnar messed up on the shooting star press near the end and suffered a mild concussion. This match earns my respect in every way.The bottomline: Buy this DVD. (...)

reviewText: Every year I rent Wrestlemania and to tell the truth, this event was way better than WM18! This event had Ashanti and Limp Bizkit performing, it even had the Miller Lite Catfight girls! Here are the matches and what I thought about them.Cruiserweight Championship matchMatt Hardy vs. Rey MysterioGreat opener with a lot of high flying moves and with a great ending.Undertaker vs. Big Show & A-TrainNot one of the Undertaker's best match at a Wrestlemania but still good, even though it was a little too short. Nathan Jones even makes an appearance towards the end of the match.Triple Threat match for the Women's ChampionshipVictoria vs. Jazz vs. Trish StratusGreat match with a lot of action. Better than last years Wrestlemania triple threat women's title match.Triple Threat tag team match for the Tag Team ChampionshipsRhyno & Chris Benoit vs. Team Angle vs. Los GuerrerosLittle bit of a let down match. This match was too short with terrible action and a terrible ending. Terrible match of the night.Shawn Michaels vs. Chris JerichoAwesome match, even though it was too long. Chirs Jericho's best match at a Wrestlemania ever.Fatal Four Way Catfight matchI'm not going to list the names, but this match was funny but really stupid. But the women looked so hot!Heavyweight Championship matchTriple H vs. Booker TGood match with a lot of competitive wrestling, I even laughed when J.R lost his temper at Ric Flair. The ending could of been better.Street FightVince McMahon vs. Hulk HoganBrutal match with some good spots. Not Vince's best street fight ever, but it was better than his one with Ric Flair at the Royal Rumble. Great spot with the ladder and table. Rowdy Roddy Piper even makes a surprise appearance. To me this match was Hogan's best match at a Wrestlemania.Stone Cold Steve Austin vs. The RockOkay match with the Rock finally defeating his long time rival at a Wrestlemania. This was a classic match that needed to be seen.Undisputed Championship matchKurt Angle vs. Brock LesnarGood technical wrestling from beginning to end. Not the best main event at a Wrestlemania, but still good. Brock's Shooting Star Press was amazing and the ending with Kurt and Brock shaking hands was a sight to see.So there you have it, to me this was the 3rd best Wrestlemania ever! Can't wait for Wrestlemania 20!

reviewText: Wrestlemania 19 was probably the best PPV of 2003.  All the matches were good, featuring 5 main event caliber matches.  ThisDVD is actually a 2 disc set.1. Matt Hardy vs. Rey Mysterio (Cruiserweight Title)Good way to kick off the show.  I wasn't expecting a lot from this match, but it didn't deliver.  Don't get me wrong, it was still good, but not what was expected.  The match is very short.  (7.5/10)2. A-Train & Big Show vs. The Undertaker (Handicap Match)Nathan Jones was supposed to be Undertaker's partner, but he was injured backstage by the F.B.I.  This was actually a good match, led by Taker putting on a great performance.  Good ending.  (7.5/10)3. Trish Stratus vs. Jazz vs. Victoria (Women's Title)I am not a fan of women's wrestling, but this was actually a really good match.  It may be the best women's match I have ever seen.  Very well-done match.  Kudos to the Divas.  (8/10)4. Los Guerrero's vs. Shelton Benjamin & Charlies Haas vs. Chris Benoit & Rhyno (WWE Tag Title/Triple Threat)It is interesting to see how far Eddie Guerrero and Chris Benoit went from this PPV to Wrestlemania 20.  I expected a lot from this match, but didn't get what I wanted.  Probably the worst match of the night, but don't let that persuade you.  It was still a good match.  (7/10)5. Shawn Michaels vs. Chris JericoGreat match.  Match of the night in my opinion.  I love seeing good straight-up, no stipulation matches with no titles on the line.  These two built up a good fued and went at it in a great match.  There are many near falls and reversals.  Second best match of the year in my opinion, only behind Angle/Benoit from Royal Rumble.  (9.5/10)6. Triple H vs. Booker T (World Heavyweight Championship)Good effort by both men.  I though this match would be a little better, but it was still very good.  Triple H pulls out all the stops like usual.  He even uses the Indian Death Lock.  Nice to see Booker T use the Houston Hangove.  Good match.  (8.5/10)7. Vince McMahon vs. Hulk Hogan (Street Fight)Great beef going into this match.  I knew this match was going to be good, but what we got was great.  Amazing, bloody effort by both men.  There is just so much emotion in this match.  Good spot when Vince jumps off a ladder and leg-drops Hogan through an announce table.  Surprise appearance by Roddy Piper and Shane McMahon.  Look for the face Vince makes when he comes up from under the ring with the lead pipe.  (9/10)8. The Rock vs. Stone Cold Steve AustinThese two have such great chemistry together.  This was another classic between the two.  It is one of the top 5 matches of the year in my opinion.  Great match, with a lot of near falls and a great finish.  It is Austin's last match to date.  (9.5/10)9. Kurt Angle vs. Brock Lesnar (WWE Title)This could have been an amazing match, but unfortunately Angle was hurt with a neck injury.  It was still one of the top ten matches of the year in my opinion.  Angle put his life on the line to wrestle in this match.  This is a technical, suplex classic.  The ending is amazing with Lesnar almost killing himself.  Very scary to watch.  (9.5/10)The best extra feature on this DVD is RAW the next night when Goldberg makes his WWE debut.  Very cool.  Definately pick up this DVD.  All the matches are good, especially the 5 main event caliber matches.Overall Rating:  9.5/10

reviewText: This was a very solid show. There were fireworks in the beginning. I was there.Cruiserweight Championship:Matt Hardy V.1(Champion) w/ Shannon Moore vs. Rey MysterioThis match was surprisingly short, but good. Shannon Moore carried the entire affair. ***Undertaker vs. A-Train and Big ShowNot as horrible, horrible, waste of time as I suspected. Nathan Jones kicked Big Show, and all was made right. Undertaker really put A-Train in his  place. ***Women's Championship:Victoria (Champion) w/ Steven Richards vs. Trish Stratus vs. JazzThis match, while not stratusfying, was the best women's match I've seen. Disappointing ending, but what're you gonna do (not let Felina debut, that's for darned sure). Steven bops himself on the head. ****WWE Tag Team Championship:Team Angle (Champions) vs. Los Guerreros vs. Chris Benoit & RhynoThank God for you, Team Angle. You do NOT suck. Neither does Eddie and Chavo's new entrance video. ***1/2"HBK" Shawn Michaels vs. "Y2J" Chris JerichoBest match of the night. A Macho Man vs. Ricky Steamboat, if ever there was one, aside from the original. For this not to be nominated for match of the year would be sodomy, plain and simple. *****Limp Bizkit Concert ***Catfight: Torrie Wilson vs. Stacy Keibler vs. Catfight GirlsVery entertaining until screwjob ending. **** (for entertainment and sheer technical mastery)World Championship:Triple H (Champion) w/ Ric Flair vs. Booker TGood match, but with a pace similar to something out of WrestleMania 6 or 7. Cool Houston Hangover, but not much following except a pedigree. ***Street Fight:Vince McMahon vs. Hulk HoganMuch better than anticipated, with some cool high spots and excellent geriatric bumps. Roddy Piper shocked the world by making his triumphant return, only to bop Hogan on the head. ****1/2The Rock vs. Stone ColdBetter than WreslteMania XV, not as good as X-7. Stone Cold was clearly mentally and physically, well, not there. Surprising ending that seemed rather anti-climactic. ****WWE Championship:Kurt Angle (Champion) vs. Brock LesnarVery good match (considering the champ had a broken neck) with some excellent spots. Brock misses a shooting star press and bops himself on the head. ****1/2In conclusion, it was the best WrestleMania in years, with many celebrities, many surprises, and many people getting bopped on the head.

reviewText: Wrestlemania is the most important Pay Per View of any given year.  It has the biggest matches and this is what people will be talking about years later.  While big things can happen at other events, everything is magnified because it happened at Wrestlemania.  Also, because the show is this big, there are extra things going on.  Limp Bizkit performed two songs (Rollin, and Crack Addict).  I was underwhelmed by both.  The Miller Lite Catfight Girls had a pillow fight that ended up involving Torrie Wilson and Stacy Keibler.  This was very boring and a complete waste of time.  The most important part of the event, though, is the wrestling...and this is very good.1. Cruiserweight Championship: Matt Hardy V.1(Champion) w/ Shannon Moore vs. Rey MysterioI really wish that these two men were given a longer chance to work and show their stuff.  This could have been an amazing match and help give the Cruiserweight division a much needed push.  Given the length of this match, it was fine.  Should have been longer, but that isn't exactly up to me.  Mysterio is always a joy to watch and Matt Hardy has one of the more interesting characters that has come around in a while.  A short, but solid match.2. Undertaker vs. A-Train and Big ShowNathan Jones was originally slotted to be the tag team partner for Undertaker, but he was pulled at the last minute.  Probably a wise decision since all reports say that Jones is very weak in the ring.  Undertaker was 10-0 at Wrestlemania going into this match.  A-Train (formerly Albert) and the Big Show could potentially be a real powerhouse tag team (not necessarily a good team, but if used correctly, it could work....).  Undertaker worked really hard to pull a good match out of this one, and while it wasn't going to measure up to some of the other matches on the card, it was decent considering it was a match with all big men.3. Women's ChampionshipVictoria (Champion) w/ Steven Richards vs. Trish Stratus vs. JazzThe women's division is getting stronger and the ring work is getting better.  Trish is the hardest working woman in the division, Jazz is the most talented (she could be wrestling men in athletic matches), and Victoria has a lot of promise (with a very interesting character).  While I'd like to see a feud between Jazz and Victoria, Trish is very popular.  A Triple Threat match is sloppier by its nature, but this was actually pretty good.  The ring work was quite good.  The only thing the women's division needs is a better announcer to sell the work.  Lawler's constant comments about puppies and the appearance of the women only serves to demean the disvision and makes it difficult to be taken seriously.4. WWE Tag Team Championship:Team Angle (Champions) vs. Los Guerreros vs. Chris Benoit & RhynoWith Edge out with a broken neck, Rhyno was subbed in to be Benoit's partner.  While Benoit should be main eventing, he is thrown in a tag match.  He seriously needs to be pushed back up the card again.  Ignoring that, we have the match.  The rookie team of Team Angle (Shelton Benjamin and Charlie Haas) are the champions and while they are still green, they are improving in every match.  Their amateur background shows and helps a lot for their ringwork.  Los Guerreros (Eddie and Chavo) is the hottest team in the WWE right now.  Benoit is incapable of turning in a bad performance.  While I would prefer a straight up match, this was just short of stellar.  Very good work here.5. Shawn Michaels vs. Chris JerichoThis is a dream match.  Since returning last year at Summerslam, HBK has had some fantastic matches (in the few that he has been in).  Wrestling with a broken back (partially fixed), Michaels is taking a lot of risk, but it is very nice to see him back in the ring.  Jericho used to be compared to HBK (and to be honest, they have a lot in common).  This was the match of the night, and perhaps should be up for Match of the Year.  It is that good.  A slow, but deliberate start to the match and Michaels and Jericho try to one-up each other with every move.  The match picks up near the end and it is just fantastic!6. World ChampionshipTriple H (Champion) w/ Ric Flair vs. Booker TBooker T needs to stay at the top of the card on RAW.  HHH has been maligned by the Internet Wrestling Community (rightly or wrongly), but this match was not one of his squashes.  Following the Jericho/Michaels classic, this match pales in comparison.  As a whole, though, this was decent enough.  It is one of the weaker matches, but there has been some stellar matches at this event.  Booker showed some good work in this match and used a move he hadn't used in some time (the Houston Hangover).  Not bad, but nothing special.7. Vince McMahon vs. Hulk HoganSay what you will, but this match was pretty entertaining.  The reason is because of the real life history between Hogan and McMahon.  They've been in business together for a long time and over time there have been some tensions.  They have played this perfectly on Smackdown and while this isn't going to be a wrestling classic, it was entertaining.  When in the ring, McMahon works very hard for his company.  How many other 50 year old owners would allow their faces to be bloody and give a leg drop off a ladder through a table?  Not many, I think, but Vince McMahon did.8. The Rock vs. Stone Cold Steve AustinThis is their third meeting at Wrestlemania.  Austin won the first two meetings.  This wasn't the classic confrontation that we've come to expect.  Rock has been in and out of wrestling, splitting his time with Hollywood and while he is pure entertainment, some of his luster is gone.  Austin is the same way.  He is working hurt, nearing 40 years old (seems to be the mark of death for quality wrestling), and hasn't been a fresh character in several years (since the Invasion angle).  Still, this is fantasy booking and there is something intriguing about Austin/Rock III.  Nothing special, but still entertaining in its own way (Rock as a heel is the most entertaining you'll get outside the ring).9. WWE Championship:Kurt Angle (Champion) vs. Brock LesnarThis is the glory match, the true main event.  This is the match I've been waiting for.  This could be destined to be a classic.  Two men with extensive amateur backgrounds going at it for the main event.  Angle is the best wrestler in the business today.  Lesnar is up and coming.  This wasn't quite as great as I had hoped, but was the second best match of the night (Jericho/Michaels).  Lesnar does not string together his moves as well as he will in 5 years.  This still might have been a classic had Lesnar hit the Shooting Star Press.  Instead he landed on his head and gave himself a concussion.  This lowers the match to just be a great match and one of the best of the year.I love watching wrestling, and I love Wrestlemania.  There is just something special about the event.  I'm not going to say what is and is not the best ever, but I am perfectly happy with buying this DVD and I'm glad that I have it in my collection.  That should count for something.

reviewText: The grandaddy of them all "Wrestlemania" invades Safeco Field in Seattle as the fans get to witness 5 championship matches and a contest 20 years in the making as Vince McMahon takes on Hulk Hogan.Disc 1-WWE Cruiserweight Championship, Matt Hardy (Champion) w/Shannon Moore vs. Rey Mysterio: It starts out hot with Rey hitting a corkscrew splash over the top onto Matt and more quick offense, before he gets hit by Moore on the outside. Matt takes over, Rey counters with a unique pin but gets a Side Effect shortly after, then Matt works on Rey's back. After a bit Rey makes his comeback, Moore trips him up, but Rey kicks out of the Twist of Fate, Matt counters a roll through, holds the ropes and covers Rey to win the match. 6/10.-We get a live performance from Limp Bizkit as they sing Rollin and Undertaker rides his bike to the ring for the following match.-Handicap Match, Undertaker vs. Big Show & A-Train: After Taker's partner Nathan Jones was taken out prior to the event, the phenom was forced to contend with two of the biggest in pro wrestling. He did well taking out both men with some power moves and unexpected submission wrestling, Show & A-Train do work over Taker for a bit. Nathan Jones does come down, knocking out Show in the aisleway, then hits a big kick on A-Train in the ring, Taker hits the Tombstone and covers. 5/10.-Triple Threat Match for the WWE Women's Championship, Victoria (Champion) w/Stevie Richards vs. Jazz vs. Trish Stratus: Jazz takes it to both women from the opening bell, locks on a neck stretch then they battle on the outside before Victoria hits a flipping leg drop for two, then Jazz also hits one for two but both pins get broken up. The pace stays pretty fast with each lady almost winning, Jazz hits an impressive powerbomb for two, then Trish takes over, hitting the Stratus-sphere. Jazz locks on a single leg boston crab. then an STF and a double arm lock into a facebuster all on Trish. Stevie comes in with a chair, but hits the rope and it goes into his face, Trish fights out of the Widow's Peak, hits the chick kick and wins the title. 7/10.-Triple Threat Match for the WWE Tag Team Championship, Team Angle (Champions) vs. Los Guerreros vs. Rhyno & Chris Benoit: Good contest here, the pace rarely slows down, there's good wrestling between 5 of the guys, minus Rhyno. Tons of double teaming, near falls and you didn't know which team was gonna win, loved the face/off between the two long time friends Eddie Guerrero and Chris Benoit. The closing moments were great as Haas and Chavo get the Gore from Rhyno and Shelton sneaks in and covers Chavo to retain the titles. 7/10.-Shawn Michaels vs. Chris Jericho: The build up for this one was very well done. Its one of the best Wrestlemania matches ever, after some early wrestling it becomes a series of one-upping as each guy hits big move after big move and Jericho really shines here as he was wrestling his idol and Michaels proved he was still Mr. Wrestlemania. Jericho worked on Shawn's back with backbreakers and the Walls of Jericho, also hitting his version of Sweet Chin Music, Michaels kept battling back and eventually hits a roll-up out of the corner and pins Chris for three. 11/10. Loved the post match handshake and hug then Jericho hits a lowblow on Shawn and leaves the ring.-Pillow Fight, Stacy Keibler & Torrie Wilson vs. The Miller Lite Catfight Girls: Its basically a segment and a lame boring one at that, yes all 4 women look good but it wasn't needed on the card.-World Heavyweight Championship Match, Triple H (Champion) vs. Booker T: Such a great and forgotten match, Booker was in rare form breaking out the Harlem Hangover rolling leg drop from the top rope and just taking it to the Game. Trips had a good showing here, even using an Indian Deathlock submission and hitting his usual moves, Flair of course interferes on Trips behalf even putting his foot on the rope when Booker had the champ beaten. Booker goes for a kick but his leg gives out, Trips hits the pedigree and makes the cover to retain his title. 10/10.-Street Fight, Hulk Hogan vs. Vince McMahon: I personally enjoyed this match, as both guys did work hard though Vince did the best in selling to Hulk and making the crowd hate him so much. There were some good weapon usage, including a vicious chair shot Hogan gave Vince on the outside, but the best spot was Vince hitting a leg drop off the ladder onto Hulk through the announce table, soon after we get a very creepy shot of Vince rising up from the floor with a pipe in hand. While both were down in the ring, Roddy Piper makes a shocking appearance and hits Hogan with the pipe, but he won't stay down. Hogan ends up hitting three leg drops and makes the cover to win this intense match, 9/10.Disc 2-The Rock vs. Stone Cold Steve Austin: This was the second best of their trilogy and pretty emotional as this was Austin's last match. Plenty of brawling in and out of the ring, Rock was in full heel mode even doning Austin's vest at one point. It seemed like a very personal match here, more so than their previous encounter throughout the years. Austin did have his moments but it was Rock's night here and after 3 Rock Bottoms the Rock finally beat Austin at Wrestlemania. 10/10.-WWE Championship Match, Kurt Angle (Champion) vs. Brock Lesnar: Great main event, great wrestling, just great everything. Plenty of submission moves are used by both men and each one almost has the other beat on numerous occasions. Loved the fact that Angle went totally gung-ho during the match, despite the fact that he needed neck surgery. Lesnar goes for a shooting star press and doesn't quite get the distance to hit Angle and Lesnar seems to jack his neck really, really, really bad, then Angle goes for the cover but Brock kicks out and somehow hits an F-5 on Angle, the third of the match for the win, to become the WWE champion for the second time. 11/10. On a side note, being from Washington, this PPV was in Seattle, Wa., and when I saw this live on PPV I honestly thought as did the crowd that Lesnar had broken his neck and after the match he didn't look like he knew where he was.Extras on Disc 2-Wrestlemania 3rd Degree: A backstage look at the Wrestlemania XIX card where Michael Cole & Tazz host and talk to some of the competitors about the matches they will be in. Good piece here.The Road To Wrestlemania-Wrestlemania Press Conference in Seattle, 9/24/02: Just highlights of the announcing of Wrestlemania in Seattle.-Edge's Wrestlemania Media Tour: Due to being out with a neck injury WWE superstar Edge decided to film some of his time out in the city of Seattle including being on some radio shows.-Wrestlemania Press Conference in New York City: Some highlights of another conference hyping Wrestlemania.Wrestlemania Weekend-Trish Stratus-Full Axxess: We see some clips of fans enjoying the Wrestlemania fan axxess as Trish hosts this look inside.Sunday Night Heat, World Tag Team Championship Match, Chief Morley & Lance Storm vs. Kane & Rob Van Dam (Champions): The Dudley's are at ringside in the corner of Storm and Morley, albeit reluctantly. Its not a bad match, cool spot with Kane hitting a big dive over the top onto both Storm and Morley, during and back from the commercial break RVD gets worked over. RVD goes for the frog splash, Morley gets hit by Kane and while on the outside The Dudley's come in and 3D Lance Storm, but Bubba elbowed RVD, put Storm on him and the champs retain. 5/10.-Attack on Nathan Jones on Sunday Night Heat: Tommy Dreamer is backstage talking to Jones, who gives chase when Nunzio steals his wallet. Show & A-Train attack Jones and leave him out cold in the shower.-Post Match Comments from Victoria, Rey Mysterio, A-Train, Nathan Jones, Stacy Keibler & Torrie Wilson-Wrestlemania Retro: Some superstars talk about their favorite Wrestlemania moments, including Stone Cold, DDP, Trish Stratus, Shawn Michaels and others.-Wrestlemania Featurettes from WWE Confidential, showing clips from the first PPV, celebrity moments, Hogan & Andre, Hogan's best moments at Wrestlemania and the Undertaker's undefeated streak.-Comments on Hogan vs. McMahon from "Mean" Gene Okerlund & Bobby "The Brain" Heenan-Wrestlemania Promotional Spots-Miller Lite Catfight Girls Vignettes-Mr. McMahon Training Vignettes-3/31/03, Raw, Goldberg's WWE Debut: The Rock is in the ring cutting a promo in classic heel mode, running down the fans and saying he has beaten everyone and there is nothing left for him to do. Goldberg's music hit to a big reaction, he hits the ring, says The Rock is next and spears him, then leaves the ring.This was one of the forgetten Wrestlemania's as its quite good, the main event matches are top notch and besides the handicap match everything else is above average.

reviewText: The Cruiserweight title match between Matt Hardy & Rey Mysterio was sweet but short mainly becuase of Shannon Moore's interference. The Handicap match between The Undertaker & the team of The Big Show & A-Train was not great but pretty good and the same goes for the Jazz-Trish Stratus-Victoria-3 way Women's title match. The 3 way tag team bout for the Smackdown tag team titles had great wrestling for a 3 way tag bout. The HBK-Y2J match was the showstealer of Wrestlemania. The Pillow Fight between Stacy Keibler & Torrie Wilson against The Miller Lite Catfight Girls was sloppy,messy & pointless. The HHH-Booker T-World's title match was pretty good for a Triple H PPV title match. The Hulk Hogan-VKM streetfight was a bloody,hard-fought brawl. The Grudge match between The Rock & Steve Austin while not as good as their past bouts,it was still a good match. The Brock Lesnar-Kurt Angle-WWE title match was a back-and-fourth,high-tech,solid match even with the messed up shooting star press by Brock. I give this PPV a 8 out of 10.

reviewText: I have been a wrestling fan since 1996 and have watched all kinds of wrestling. I have a wrestling DVD/VHS collection spanning over 50 all together. This is the most complete and accurate review of this DVD you will find. I hope you find this review helpful; remember to vote helpful or not helpful.(Note-Each DVD I review has a "Match of the DVD" award somewhere in it.)Wrestlemania XIXThis event was amazing from top to bottom. The staging and extremely long ramp are cool. This is probably one of the best Wrestlemania's you could buy. It was almost perfect. Buy this as soon as you can.Disc 1WWE Cruiserweight ChampionshipMatt Hardy(c) w/Shannon Moore VS Rey MysterioGreat Opener. This match gets you excited for the rest of the event. There is a lot of highflying action including: corkscrew moonsaults, Splash Mountain Bombs to Hurricanrunnas, and much more. This is one of the best openers I've ever seen.RATING-9/10Betweens these two matches, Limp Bizkit performs "Rollin".Handicap MatchUndertaker VS Big Show & A-TrainThis match was originally a tag match that consisted of Undertaker teaming with Nathan Jones. Nathan Jones was attacked by Show and A-Train (with the help of Nunzio) and could not compete in the event. The match is pretty solid which I honestly didn't expect. Nathan Jones makes an appearance near the end and deals out a nice spin kick.RATING-7/10Triple-Threat- Women's ChampionshipVictoria(c) w/ Steven Richards VS Trish Stratus VS JazzThere aren't really a lot of really good women's matches in WWE. This match is awesome though. Victoria does a cool moonsault. Jazz uses her power to control most of the match. The ending seemed a little weak though.RATING-8.5/10Triple-Threat Tag- WWE Tag Team ChampionshipTeam Angle(c) VS Los Guerreros VS Rhyno & BenoitBenoit returns to Wrestlemania afterWWE WrestleMania X8due to a broken neck. This is a solid match-up and keeps the action going well.RATING-8/10Shawn Michaels VS Chris JerichoI might get a lot of hate for saying this, but this match is over rated constantly. It was a great match with a great storyline. The match wasn't that amazing though. I enjoyed it and I know everyone else will enjoy it, but don't get sucked into the hype machine or you will be let down. Still, the story is amazing and the match is great. It is just not a perfect 10.RATING-9/10Limp Bizkit performs "Crack Addict" between these two matches.Pillow FightCatfight Girls VS Stacy Keibler VS Torrie WilsonSomewhat funny but really not much here. No rating because it's not much of a match.World Heavyweight ChampionshipTriple H(c) VS Booker TI love this match. Triple H and Booker T use every move in their arsenal, even using some new moves. Triple H works over Booker's leg most of the match and Booker sells it very well. This match is very well done and you will love it.RATING-9/10Street Fight- 20 Years in the MakingHulk Hogan VS Vince McMahonThis isn't the best street fight ever, not even Vince's best street fight, but it is still really good. There is a really good announcer table spot done by Vince. A lot of blood is shed in this match. There is also an appearance by another WWE legend near the end of the match.RATING-8/10Disc 2Stone Cold Steve Austin VS The Rock(Match of the Night Award)This match is amazing. A lot of brawling like the usual Austin/Rock confrontations. Finishers are used like crazy. What's funny is this isn't even there best match. They had matches at two other Wrestlemania's:WWE WrestleMania XV - The Ragin' ClimaxandWWE WrestleMania X-Seven.RATING-9.5/10WWE ChampionshipKurt Angle VS Brock LesnarThis is a very good match. Lots of suplexes and finishers. Slow-paced but the match works well that way. The ending is sickening and hard to watch, luckily Lesnar is okay. These two would go on to fight many more matches including their next one-on-one PPV match atWWE SummerSlam 2003.RATING- 8/10Extras Include-Wrestlemania 3rd DegreeThe Road to WrestlemaniaWrestlemania WeekendWorld Tag Team Championship (from Heat)Post Match CommentsWrestlemania RetroWrestlemania FeaturesComments on Hogan VS McMahonWrestlemania Promotional SpotsThe Catfight Girls (Promos)McMahon TrainingGoldberg Returns (Night after WM)

reviewText: By far, Wrestlemania XIX was the greatest of all time! The grandest event, the showcase of the immortals, the year 2003 shall never ever be forgotton! A fast-paced, furious and high-flying Wrestlemania and perhaps the best ever matches to grace a PPV!WWE Cruiserweight ChampionshipMatt Hardy v Rey MysterioAwesome opener! The 54,097 fans were really hyped and buzzing for what was in store. This high-flying combination of death-defying moves stunned the Seattle crowd as Rey Mysterio made his Wrestlemania debut and put on his greatest performance yet. Great way to kick off a PPVUndertaker & Nathan Jones v A Train & Big ShowIn his 11th Wrestlemania, the Deadman faced the unstoppable team of A Train and Big Show, two of the biggest heels in history. A hard-fought battle with the in ring debut of Nathan Jones. Sloober Knocker of a Tag Team Match!WWE Womans ChampionshipVictoria v Trish v JazzFast paced action here, great spots for all three Divas! Fun match that made Trish's names even bigger!WWE Tag Team ChampionshipLos Guerreros v Team Angle v Chris Benoit & RhynoExcellent Tag Match! Chris Benoit, Eddie Guerrero and Rhyno are at the top of their game and this great match proved that. This action was so fast, it was hard to catch all that was going on. Great ending too!Chris Jericho v Shawn MichaelsThis was a show stealer!!! This fantastic battle is perhaps one of the greatest I have ever seen! Two of WWE's most inspirational superstars, HBK and Y2J finally face each other inside the squared circle after months of anticipation. This was a classic match with loads of near falls and high flying action. Jericho's greatest match to date and this will sure to be 2003 Match of the Year! A Wrestlemania dreamWorld ChampionshipTriple H v Booker TThe fans were still buzzing after the Jericho-Michaels Match so their was not as much hype coming into this one. But still, great techinal battle to pace things up. Triple H and Booker T have great chemistry but Ric Flair is still the dirtest player in the game. Unstoppable actionStreet Fight20 Years in the MakingThe Battle in SeattleHulk Hogan v Mr McMahonAll i can say is that in all the years I have watch wrestling, I have never seen two legends in the businnes fight with so much heart and desire for the crowd. This was a bloody, brutal and dangerous street fight. Great spots all the way, McMahon's leg drop from the top of the ladder shrined out by all a long way. Hogan proved he still runs wild and McMahon proved he can still fight with the best. Bloody as hell and another Match of the Year for 2003!The Rock v Stone ColdAfter all their battles in the past and their two classics at Wrestlemanias, this has to be their greatest showdown ever. This is another classic and another Match of the Year! This years Wrestlemania had so many great main events that it is hard to choose the best. The Rock and Austin are in their prime and put on a great near fall display of fast paced action, the way the WWE fans like it now! Huge pop for both superstars. Great match with both icons using each others finishing moves to make this classic even betterWWE ChampionshipBrock Lesner v Kurt AngleDREAM MATCH, SHOW STEALER, MATCH OF THE YEAR and everything else. What a classic wrestling match. 100% wrestling. Two of the greatest wrestlers in WWE history, Olympic Champion Kurt Angle and NCAA Championship Brock Lesner square up in the most techinal battle you will ever see! The best ever Wrtestlemania main event, one for the ages! Lesner's Shooting Star Press is fantastic!So, with a musical performance by limp Bizkit also, this was the greatest Wrestlemania of all time.
summary: The Greatest Wrestlemania Of All Time!!

reviewText: X-8 was probably the most overhyped, overrated WM of all time, so I went into XIX hoping for a lot better, but it was a let down. It was better than X-8 and some other WM's I can think of, but fell short, I'll get to that in a minute. The set on the other hand, was amazing.The GoodJericho and Michaels was the show stealer. Simply an amzing match.Angle vs. Lesnar was an awesome match, but Brock botched SSP really ruined the ending.Rock vs. Austin. Rock carried this thing, a great match, but lacked the magic that previous Rock-Austin matches had.The MediocreRey vs. Mattitude. That was too short of a match and it ended as it was about to get good.Triple H vs. Booker T. There is no explanation why Booker didn't go over here. Triple H took the offense and drug the match down, Booker for his part was on fire. Disturbing booking and politics bothered me here big time.Benoit/Rhyno vs. Los Guerreros vs. Haas/Benjiman. This was another match that was way too short and rushed.Trish vs. Jazz vs. VictoriaIt was a decent match, but it was also predictable.The BadWhat did I do, Oh Lord, to get Limp Bizkit to waste 6 minutes of my life. Not counting that performance that brought Taker to the ring. WWE's favorite band, well this is the company who's owner thought the XFL and WBF was a good idea.The Cat fight, we'd be better sniffing cat poo. Plenty of other DVD's of Kitana Baker doing better.I was emotionally traumatize by the fact I had to see Coach without his pants.Taker vs. Albert/The Big ShowGodawful borefest, but the good new is we didn't see Nathan Jones, oh wait...darnit!Hulk Hogan vs. Vince McMahonJust plain awful, as it was time to rid the WWE once and for all of Hogan. Vince for his part was convincing and the only reason to watch this match is because of him. However, this match was way too long for me to watch two old men duke it out.ExtrasForgettable extras, but check out Victoria's funny post WM comments. There's a forgettable Tag Team title match between RVD/Kane vs. Lance Storm & Sean Morely (Val Venis). The use WM blowfest, some intresting but useless stuff. At least WM X-8 gave us Warrior vs. Hogan match from VI and an intresting interview with Vinny Mac on Byte This (WWE Internet Talk Show).

reviewText: WRESTLEMANIA XIX the first Wrestlemania under the WWE banner co-producedby the two WWE Brands RAW and SMACKDOWN! and this is one of the bestWrestlemania's of all time. There were nine matches booked for thisevent and they are:WWE Cruiserweight Championship (4 out of 5)Matt Hardy (c) vs. Rey Misterio-Fast paced A Great Opener for the biggest show of the year!Undertaker vs. Big Show/A-Train (3 out of 5)-Taker proving he can still go and watch out for Nathan JonesBack Spinning Heel KickTriple Threat World Womens Championship (3 out of 5)Victoria (c) vs. Trish Stratus vs. Jazz-Decent Womens World title MatchTriple Threat WWE Tag-Team Championship (3 out of 5)Team Angle (c) vs. Los Guerreros vs. Rhyno/Benoit-Like the WOmens decent Match cept for the ending.Chris Jericho vs. Shawn Michaels (5 out of 5)-This starts the actual Wrestlemania, Michaels/Y2Jmatch was awesome, its like wrestling yourself boththis guys know what their opponent's moves are!RAW World Heavyweight Championship (4 out of 5)Triple H (c) vs. Booker T-Triple H proving to the world that he deserves theWorld Heavyweight Belt. check out his applying the age-oldindian deathlock, good variations you have to see it for yourself.Street Fight 20 Years in The Making (5 out of 5)Mr. McMahon vs. Hulk Hogan-20 years in the making and it dosen't disappoint I think J.R. said itbest "Unbelievable Street Fight". This match in view stole the showThe Rock vs Stone Cold Steve Austin (5 out of 5)-The Final act of the Austin/Rock Feud and dosen't disappoint.Great way for Austin to end his wrestling career, lots of action.Smackdown! WWE Championship (5 out of 5)Kurt Angle (c) vs. Brock Lesnar-And now the encore! fans waiting for almost a year Lesnar/Anglegreat amateur style wrestling for the coveted SmackDown! WWE Championship,great Shooting star press too bad it didn't connect.the last 5 matches is worth the ppv itself with guest appearanceby the Millar Cat Fight Girls with Special performance by Limp Biskitthis one deserves a place in your Wrestling DVD or Video Library!

reviewText: When I think back on all the WWE shows that I have seen, Wrestlemania 19 definately comes to mind. As far as the PPV itself goes, the card was well rounded for the most part. For those fans who are interested in the classic technical side of wrestling, you cannot go wrong with Shawn Michaels vs Chris Jericho. This had to be one of the best matches I have ever seen period. Another match that falls under the technical category would be the main event between Brock Lesnar and Kurt Angle. Both are very skilled mat technicians and Brock put on a good performance despite the fact that he is a big guy. He is very agile for his size. For those fans who want to see an all out brawl, Hulk Hogan vs Vince McManon and Stone Cold Steve Austin vs The Rock are guaranteed to make you happy. Hulk Hogan and Vince both put on great performances. I was very suprised too, because they usually can't wrestle their way out of a paper bag. This match made me gain a lot of respect for Vince, because you have got to admire the owner of the company actually getting involved and trying to entertain the fans. The WWE Tag Team championship match featuring Team Angle, Los Guerreros, and Chris Benoit/Rhyno was an all around good match. Perhaps the most underated match of the night was Triple H vs Booker T.Having 6 good matches out of 9 possible is pretty good by WWE standards. Most WWE shows feature a few good matches combined with a majority of average matches. That is why I consider Wrestlemania 19 to be well rounded. However, the reason why I gave a 5 star rating, is because of the DVD itself. The WWE actually put out a DVD with great extras. They include Goldberg's debut on RAW the night after Wrestlemania, Vince Mcmanon training vignettes, 10 stars talking about their favorite Wrestlemania moments, post match interviews and more.If you are a fan of the WWE, there is no way you can pass this up. The excellent Wrestlemania and the outstanding extras make this a must own.A solid 5 stars...

reviewText: This is Mudd.  This is one of the gretest Wrestlemania's ever and it is a must have DVD.Matt Hardy vs. Rey Mysterio for the Cruiserweight Title.  This match was a great way to kick off Wrestlemania.  I really though Rey was gonna pull it off but Matt retains the belt. (7.5/10)The Undertaker vs. A-Train & Big Show was a not as good as the Cruiserweight Match because this match was slow and it got boring at points.  Taker picks up the win to keep a perfect record at Wrestlemania. (7/10)Trish Stratus vs. Victoria vs. Jazz for the Women's Title.  This match had some good spots and some bad spots and Trish won the Women's Title. (6.5/10)Chris Benoit & Rhyno vs. Team Angle vs. Los Guerreros for the WWE Tag Team Titles.  This was very faced paced action and it had some great moves and this match was overall pretty good.  Team Angle retain the belts. (7.5/10)Shawn Michaels vs. Chris Jericho was a excellent match that will never be forgotten.  This match was long but it delievered.  HBK & Y2J put on a classic with HBK winning in the end. (9.5/10)Triple H vs. Booker T for the World Title.  This was nothing near Eddie vs. Kurt at Wrestlemania XX.  The reason I say this is because Eddie vs. Kurt was decided by a superstar who didn't win the Rumble.  Anyways, this was a good match and Triple H retained his belt. (8/10)Hulk Hogan vs. Mr. McMahon in a Street Fight.  This match was very bloody and the buid-up was incredible and these 2 do things I never imagine they could do.  Hogan wins then gets fired on Smackdown!  (9/10)The Rock vs. Stone Cold Steve Austin was a good match because Austin had way to much on his shoulders to put on a classic match.  The Rock picks up the win and Austin hangs it up. (8/10)Kurt Angle vs. Brock Lesnar for the WWE Title.  This was a good match but it lacked in certain areas.  Brock wins the Title after 3 F5-s and a SSP!!!! (8.5/10)This was the gretest wrestleMania ever besides WrestleMania XX.  I am a tough grader and none of the matches got 10/10.  But the Match of the Night is HBK vs. Y2J.

reviewText: In my opinion, this was the best WrestleMania of all time and the only down side was a dull, lifeless crowd (why do the WWE insist on going places like this, surely they know of places where the crowd get into it like NYC or Chicago?)Matt Hardy vs. Rey Mysterio (3/5)What else do you expect from the cruiserweight division but fantastic highflying, fast paced matches. This is one of them.Undertaker vs. Big Slow/ Albert (3/5)Neither here no there, not bad but not good either. Just a match to boost 'Taker's ego.Trish vs. Victoria vs. Jazz (4/5)The best -bar none- women's match i've ever seen and the best match so far.Eddie and Chavo vs. Team Angle vs. Benoit and Rhyno (4/5)Good all round effort, nice fast paced match, one of the best tag matches i can recall seeing.Shawn Michaels vs. Jericho (5/5)Remember how people talk about Savage vs. Steamboat or Hart vs. Bulldog or Hart vs. Austin? Add this to the list... exceptional and best Mania match in years.Triple H vs. Booker T (2/5)Triple H used to rule, and probably deserved to win this match. But boy did it suck and Booker T jobbed worse than Virgil.Hogan vs. McMahon (4/5)A very good Hogan match, one of his best efforts. Much, much better than i expected.Rock vs. Austin (5/5)They headlined Mania XV and X7 for a reason, this is why.Angle vs. Lesnar (5/5)This is the match that i wanted to see, and the only match that was worthy of a main event spot. But the fans don't get into enough. I don't think they appreciate the purpose and the point this match made but it was amazing.This or WrestleMania X-Seven must be the best, surely?
