reviewText: Don't get me wrong, it wasn't horrible. As a matter of fact, it was a solid event. Just not Wrestlemania X-7 caliber. Though some of the buildup was good, the PPV still lacked in a lot of ways.WWE Cruiserweight ChampionshipMatt Hardy-Version 1 vs. Rey MysterioWhy did they make Kidman drop the belt to Hardy at No Way Out? Kidman vs. Mysterio would have been a classic seeing as how they have faced each other in the defunct WCW. Anyway, unnecessary interference and Mysterio carried the entire match. Horrible ending. **3/4 stars.Undertaker vs. Big Show and A-TrainI thought that this would be the event to witness the debut of 6'10" Nathan Jones. Obviously, we were all mistaken. Not a bad match, but very slow considering that you have almost a combined weight of 900 lbs in the ring. Decent ending. **1/2 stars.Women's Championship:Victoria vs. Trish Stratus vs. JazzAlmost a rematch of the Triple Threat Match at last year's Wrestlemania. Some better spots in this contest, however the ending was pretty tame. **1/2 stars.WWE Tag Team Championship:Team Angle vs. Los Guerreros vs. Rhyno and Chris BenoitIf only Edge hadn't been injured. He would have possibly made this match a Match of the Year candidate. Decent match, not a great match as the commentators suggest, but okay. Good finish. **3/4 stars.Shawn Michaels vs. Chris JerichoThe streak of not having any potential Match of the Year candidates at Wrestlemania is officially over in my opinion. X-8 didn't muster up a single one, but this was the match of the night. A highly anticipated matchup that did not disappoint. The fans were in this match, with each superstar receiving their own crowd support. Excellent ending. ****1/2 stars.World Heavyweight ChampionshipTriple H vs. Booker TAnother great match, which showcased Booker T's talent and athletic ability. As a fan of both superstars, I was impressed. Didn't care for the ending, but does serve a purpose for a possible feud. **** stars.Street FightVince McMahon vs. Hulk HoganAgain, a Hogan match is the most hyped for a PPV. Not a match I was looking forward to as I remember Hogan's "performance" at last year's event. This was better, but my goodness, did it ever take forever to actually turn into a Street Fight. When it finally became what the stipulation intended, the contest was fair. Some weak spots, but the ending was shocking. **1/2 stars.Stone Cold Steve Austin vs. The RockNot as great as their brutal and classic match at Wrestlemania X-7, but still pretty entertaining. The outcome was pretty predictable, but is necessary in the buildup for the upcoming PPV. ***1/2 stars.WWE ChampionshipKurt Angle vs. Brock LesnarThe PPV was at a four-star level, up until this match. This, in my opinion could have been just as brutal as the buildup especially if this had been made a No-DQ contest. An okay match was the end result. A five minute headlock display by Kurt Angle put me momentarily to sleep and the botched Shooting Star that every reviewer has talked about had me cringe, but at the match's conclusion, I wasn't satisfied. **3/4 stars.A PPV, especially if it's a Wrestlemania should make you want to watch it again and again. But the only thing that I feel is watchable is HBK/Y2J and Booker T/Triple H. Still a solid event, but I am looking more towards Wrestlemania XX at Madison Square Garden. I have a feeling that that will be the best sports entertainment spectacle ever!!
summary: Still Not the Best Wrestlemania Ever

reviewText: This is easily one of the greatest "WrestleMania" events I've seen in its 22-and-running lineage.  The Seattle crowd was always energetic (even during some poor moments).  Limp Bizkit put on two spectacular performances.  Plenty of pyro-technics and entrance flair were used to give each match its own 'epic feel'.  And most importantly, the matches are consistently entertaining throughout.  Here's the rundown:1) Cruiserweight ChampionshipRey Mysterio vs. Matt Hardy (champion)---Mysterio enters in a Daredevil outfit, while the heavier Mattitude (Version 1.0) enters with his useless sidekick (Shannon Moore).  This is a good match that the crowd is really into, but it's way too short.  Eight minutes (including entrances) is not enough time to establish the Cruiserweight division's worth.  Still, what's here is really good."7.0 / 10"2) The Undertaker vs. Big Show & A-Train---This was supposed to be a Tag Team match, but Nathan Jones was conveniently injured.  That's okay, because at "WM", Taker deserves a solo spotlight.  Limp Bizkit performs their "Rollin'" track, the three giants enter, and off we go.  This is actually a fairly entertaining brawl between three huge athletes.  The Undertaker actually makes us believe how he could have pulled this one off alone.  Nathan Jones makes a surprise appearance and delivers some wicked kicks to Big Show and A-Train.  It surprises me to say it, but this match is a look."6.0 / 10"3) Women's ChampionshipTrish Stratus vs. Jazz vs. Victoria (champion)---We can usually count on "WrestleMania" to give us good Women's matches, and this is no exception.  Each competitor works hard to make this one work, plus Steven Richards has a hilarious chair spot.  Oh by the way, fancy entrance for Trish Stratus, which proves WWE spent a crapload of money for the entire card."7.0 / 10"4) WWE Tag Team ChampionshipsLos Guerreros vs. Chris Benoit & Rhyno vs. Team Angle (champions)---Take six of the WWE's top athletes, throw them all together in Tag Team action, and what do you get?  One heck of a good contest.  Shelton Benjamin and Charlie Haas (Team Angle) had a lot to prove as rookie superstars, and made believers out of us all.  Eddie and Chavo (Guerreros) are always good, and so they are here, yet oddly keep the cheating to an all-time low.  Chris Benoit really brings his A-game tonight, and Rhyno also makes his presence known here.  This match could've been a little bit better - something's just missing here - but this is still one very good match."7.5 / 10"5) Chris Jericho vs. Shawn Michaels---First off, Shawn Michaels' usual pyro gets upgraded to confetti cannons and TWO sets of fireworks.  Good Lord, the spectacle just keeps on coming.  As for the match...Holy cow!  What an amazing match!  These two men showcase everything: breath-taking athleticism, crisp technical skills, finisher psychology, pure charisma, and never-say-die attitude.  This is easily one of the greatest matches I've ever seen!  There's no interference, cheating is kept to a minimum, and I'm a sucker for those false finishes.  I've got nothing but praise now, but this match leaves me speechless every time I see it!"9.5 / 10" - Match Of The Year!6) Cat FightTanya Salinger & Kitana Parker (Miller Lite Girls)vs. Stacy Keibler & Torrie Wilson (WWE Divas)---Not really a match, because nobody wins and it happens on the entrance stage.  yes, these ladies are superhot, but something bothers me about this (other than it's a waste of time).  The World Tag Team Titles Match got pushed to a pre-broadcast "HEAT".  That title bout is on the DVD, but it deserved to be on the PPV show.  Anyway, gorgeous women, stupid comedy."1.0 / 10"7) World Heavyweight ChampionshipTriple H (champion) vs. Booker T---Booker T is one of the most inconsistent wrestlers I've ever seen.  He can be terrifically entertaining, but boring and uninteresting during other matches.  But the Houston challenger brings his A-game tonight, and proves why he can carry the gold.  Triple H gets a lot of criticism for being a show-stealer; but to me, he's a WWE professional who knows how to make other guys look good.  The finish is pretty weak, but otherwise it's a solid match that earns its World Heavyweight Title headline."7.0 / 10"8) Street Fight - 20 Years In The MakingHulk Hogan vs. Vince McMahon---I really don't care for this one at all.  Yes, chair shots are always amusing, and Vince's ladder spot is neat.  But this is merely a wannabe-Hardcore match with two geriatrics (or three if you include Roddy Piper).  Does anybody really believe Hogan couldn't beat Vinnie Mac?  Sadly, Hogan's worst "WM" match ever...including against Yokozuna @ "WM 9"."3.0 / 10"9) The Rock vs. Stone Cold---This is a tough one to call.  On the one hand, I recognize that Austin and Rock are two of the greatest WWE has ever had.  I realize they take superstardom to the max, and always work hard to put on a great show.  However, my other hand tells me that I've seen this match before...twice!  If you haven't seen any of their previous classic battles, then you're in for a real treat.  However, chances are you have seen those two matches.  I'm guessing most will enjoy this one, but not love it.  To me, it's a passable match with a neat "ACT III" headline written all over it."6.0 / 10"10) WWE ChampionshipKurt Angle (champion) vs. Brock Lesnar---"WM" rarely goes wrong with main events, and I'm happy to say that this is one of the best!  Both men are excellent technicians, incredibly quick, and possess an undying will to win.  One thing that stood out to me is that these two guys know how to make submission holds interesting to watch.  They're not afraid to mix some old-school pacing with some hard slams and bumps from the new-school pages.  Lesnar's shooting-star-attempt is still painful to watch, and Angle really fought his heart out to make "WrestleMania XIX" worth the four-hour running time.  Congrats to both men.  Oh, and more pyro goes off as the show comes to its fadeout."8.0 / 10"OVERALL---In addition to one of the best "WrestleMania" PPVs ever, Disc II features a plethora of extras including interviews, trailers, superstars' favorite "Mania" moments, and the hour-long teaser program "WrestleMania 3rd Degree" that aired one week before "WM XIX".  My highest recommendation possible for one of the WWE's best PPVs!

reviewText: From begin to end, the Wrestlemania XIX DVD is nothing short of great.  However it is the entire DVD that gets 5 stars, not the actual show.  Too many people Are giving WM19 5 Stars becuase of DVD Quality and extras.  The Wrestling part is not spectactular.  Don't get me wrong WM 19 is far from the Worst.  Much better than WM's 9,11,1,2,etc. but it is not the classic WM's such as 3,6,17, etc. were.  WM 19 falls in the middle somewhere.  It was held in a nice big place in Safeco Field in Seattle.  The crowd was nice and loud all night. The performance by Limp Bizkit was great as well.  The Millerlight Cat girls did a nice job. However, WM's should be graded by their matches not any extra performances at the event and extra included in DVD's, such as Goldberg's Debut following Wrestlemania, Undertaker's WM Perfect Redord, WM 3 Flashback ETC.  The match of the Night was The Icon Shawn Michaels Vs. Chris Jericho.  This Match was just terrific.  Many near falls filled with exitement.  It was one of the greatest wrestlemania matches ever seen.  The main Event did not dissapoint.  Kurt angle Vs. Brock Lesnar was just gret Wrestling for a great end.  Hogan Vs. Mcmahon was just a blood bath.  They were not really wrestling, they were just battering each other around.  The match included a suprise interference from Rowdy Roddy Piper.  This match was from two oldies with a lot animosity towards each other.  Vince Mcmahon who isn't really a wrestler went up agianst Hulk Hogan (Hogan is washed up) in fight that just seemed like two people who just wanted tw beat the hell out of each other.  This match for the most part was not what you call wrestling, but watching them beat the crap out of each other was fun.  It was no classic but fun.  Rock Vs. Austin III, was not the macth there first two were.  It was still a nice match.  It is always fun two watch these two go at it with one another.  It just did not have the same feel there first two matches had.  Even before the match, it makes you ask wonder why are these two fighting for the third time at a Wrestlemania.  Both men were not on top of their game anymore.  Also, Austin was not Austin in this match.  The WWE may have made the Rock finally beat Austin at a Wrestlemania as a punishment for Austin walking out on them months earlier.  Undertaker Went 12-0 at WM with a nice win.  Also, why were RVD and Kane not in this Wrestlemania, I heard the reason because the WWE thought would not be enought time for a match invloving them.  I was glad to see Matt Hardy Pin Rey Mysterio, Mysterio is so overated.  The rest was really mediocre and nothing more.  The DVD is a great watch but the wrestling part of it is not.
summary: The DVD Is Awesome But The Actual Show Is Not

reviewText: Wrestlemania XIX was just a tremendous event. Some say Wrestlemania X-Seven is arguably the greatest Wrestlemania ever and this Wrestlemania is the reason for the arguably part. This Wrestlemania was solid from top to bottom from beginning to end. Not a single dud or a bad match on here whatsoever. To believe it or not, to me the downside to this Wrestlemania were those stupid MillerLite catfight girls and the Torrie Wilson & Stacy Kiebler segements throughout the event leading up their little bed pillow fight. Besides them an Awesome event.1. Cruiserweight ChampionshipMatt Hardy w/ Shannon Moore vs. Rey MysterioVery fast paced match up here. Lots of interference from Moore though. Some other reviewers have said that this match was short; I think it was given a good amount of time. It did its job to pump up the crowd for the night. Very good opener. 4/52. Undertaker vs. Big Show & A-TrainNot a bad match at all. It really got exciting in the beginning with Taker hitting the chokeslam in the early going and just doing his business all over Train and Big Show. Show and Train would take some cheap shots to Taker throughout the match due to the 2 on 1 advantage. Nathan Jones would come out and give Show a wicked spinning kick to take him out. Decent match up and it had a good ending(11-0). 3.5/53. Women's ChampionshipJazz vs. Trish Stratus vs. Victoria w/ Steven RichardsThe women delivered on this night. Some pretty good spots. Victoria and Jazz would try to double team Trish but their egoes would soon get in the way. Richards added some humor to the match. Pretty fine women's match. Very watchable. 3.5/54. WWE Tag Team ChampionshipLos Guererros vs. Team Angle vs. Chris Benoit & RhynoNice tag team title match. Benoit & Eddie put on a great showing when they were in the ring together. There was some nice double team moves by Team Angle. The 3rd team really added more to the match. Rhyno hit some sickening gores in this one too. It had a sneaky ending but it all worked out good. 3.5/55. Shawn Michaels vs. Chris JerichoPhenomenal match right here. Jericho & Michaels make a great pairing in the ring together. Jericho would start working on Michael's back after applying the walls of Jericho on the outside and then just punishing Michaels' back. There were some nice counters and some good wrestling. Jericho would try to top Michaels at some points in the match by doing his moves. It had a very good ending as well, I thought it fitted in just good. Match of the night for sure. Another Wrestlemania classic match up. 5/56. World Heavyweight ChampionshipBooker T vs. Triple H w/ Ric FlairSome people really forgets about how good of a match this was. I thought this match was very good and I felt it was Wrestlemania material. Booker to me really had to prove himself in this match I thought. He really gave Hunter a run for his money in this one. There were some good brawling and some good wrestling holds. Hunter would work on Booker's leg and even applying the old school indian death lock on Booker which was very cool to see. Booker even added some high risk to the match. A very good forgotten match up right here, you will see what I mean when you watch it. 4.5/57. Street FightMr. McMahon vs. Hulk HoganThis was a fight many people have been waiting to see after when Hogan went to the WCW back in '93. McMahon would work on Hogan's arm in the beginning. The match was very brutal and very personal. Not a lot a weapons used but this was really just a good old fashion fight. This is possibably McMahon's best match in his career. You even get a suprise appeareance as well. A very insane, violent, brutal, personal match. 4/58. Stone Cold Steve Austin vs. The RockIn my opinion, being the third encounter at Wrestlemania between Rock & Austin, this was the most personal out of the three. It started out very intense and fierce. It had some good brawling and hard shots on the outside. There were some very nice counters too. Rock works on Austin's leg briefly but not that whole much. The Rock hit some very hard impact Rock Bottoms to Austin in this one. I felt the macth was a little more on the entertainment side than the wrestling side but it still was a very great match. Defiantly the last time you will ever see these two in the ring against one another and they put on a very good showing. 4.5/59. WWE ChampionshipKurt Angle vs. Brock LesnarSome say their SummerSlam match was better than this one, I disagree with that. I believe this match was the best between the two. It had a better feel and hype to it to me. There was some good suplexes and reversals. Some nice impact moves and some solid wrestling. Lesnar trys to go for a shooting star but crashes and burn and it looked like it broke Lesnar's nose. Angle also suffers a broken neck. Angle did an unbeliveable job to fight through the injury and especially after he suffer's three F5s. A great main event. Very worthy of being in any Wrestlemania. Fantastic match, you can't ask for anything else from this one. 5/5Wrestlemania XIX really went surpass the hype. An awesome event, I defiantly recommend in owning this one.
summary: Definitely a toss up with X-Seven for the Greatest Ever!

reviewText: Hello and welcome to my review on Wrestlemania XIX. I use a grading system and each match receives a grade. Then to determine how the show ranks the total of the matches scores are divided by the number of matches giving the grade and a comment about whether you should buy it or not. The grading system is as follows.Grading E- =0-6.66%E =6.66-13.32%E+ =13.32-19.98%D- =19.98-26.64%D =26.64-33.30%D+ =33.30-39.96%C- =39.96-46.62%C =46.62-53.28%C+ =53.28-59.94%B- =59.94-66.60%B =66.60-73.26%B+ =73.26-79.92%A- =79.92-86.58%A =86.58-93.24%A+ = 93.24-100%Match One-Cruiserweight Title-Matt Hardy(C)Vs Rey Mysterio-This was a nice opener and it did what it was meant to do. It was a good match except it was a little bit to short, if it had got about 12 minutes or so it would have been exceptionally good. There was a little bit too much interference from Shannon Moore but that was expected and it added a little bit to this match. Hopefully these two get a rematch with maybe a ladder match or something. My rating 7.30/10.Match Two-Handicap Match-Undertaker Vs A-Train and Big Show-Taker was putting his undefeated streak at Wrestlemania on the line and he needed a little bit of a boost so what better thing for him then to come out to his old tune "Rollin" which Limp Biskit was singing live. After getting attacked on Sunday Night Heat, Nathan Jones returned interfering in this match giving a huge spinning kick and a big boot. Taker used all his signature moves bar one in this match and it was a good show all round especially considering Show and Train aren't the greatest wrestlers but Taker made them look very good out there. My rating 7.57/10.Match Three-Triple Threat-Womens Championship-Victoria(C)Vs Jazz Vs Trish Stratus-This was an average match with the three ladies. There were lots of high flying manuevers as well as strong power ones. There was too many pinfalls broken up by the other person rather then kick outs. There was double teaming on the face by the heels, then the heels attacking each other. The finish was alrightly made with Steven Richards trying to interfere on behalf of Victoria. This was a good addition as the first of the two triple threat matches tonight. My rating 6.54/10.Match Four-Triple Threat-WWE Tag Team Championships-Charlie Haas and Shelton Benjamin(C)Vs Eddie and Chavo Guerrero Vs Rhyno and Chris Benoit-Three of these men were in the Smackdown six which is who Paul Heyman built Smackdown around late last year. The action is well paced and not to over done. Everyone did what they do best and it made it more exciting and telling what these wrestlers do. The length was perfect except it maybe should have got a little bit longer. The finish was well planned with a bit of stealing for the victory. My rating 7.80/10.Match Five-Y2J Vs Shawn"HBK"Michaels-This was HBKs return to Wrestlemania after four and a half years away from the ring. These two have been feuding since Y2J interupted HBK in December 2002. They attacked each other on numerous occasions and they will finally settle it at Wrestlemania. HBK had his own pyros on the way to ring as well as extra fireworks high up on Safeco Field during his Muscle Pose. There were lots of damaging moves done to Michaels back and lots of high flying action from HBK and lots of innovative moves from both men. There was lots of countering in this match and a couple of finishers hit here and there as well as some being countered. The ending was fairly good as it was simple with only a roll up proving good matches don't need over the top endings. My rating 9.32/10.Match Six-World Heavyweight Championship-HHH(C)Vs Booker T-Booker T won a 20 man Battle Royal the night after No Way Out to earn the shot at the World Heavyweight Championship at Wrestlemania XIX. For many weeks HHH taunted and layed the smack on Booker T. Then in the last week leading into Wrestlemania Booker gained a pinfall over HHH. Will Booker T be able to overcome all the odds and beat HHH and become the new World Heavyweight Champion? These two had a fairly long grueling match though there wasn't any blood it was still a great perfomance by both wrestlers in this match. There was a fair bit of interference in this match from Ric Flair but that always happens with HHH matches. Book and HHH pulled out all the tricks in the book as well as some great manuevers such as a wide range or kicks from Booker, the Indian Deathlock from HHH and the Houston Hangover as well as many more. There were quite a few attempts at hitting finishers but they got countered or kicked out of. The ending wasn't the greatest as it took a little to long to cover the fallen opponent to win. This was a great Raw Title match. My rating 8.80/10.Match Seven-Street Fight-Vince McMahon Vs Hulk Hogan-If Hogan loses his career is over. This was twenty years in the making. It had a lot of blood from both men as they were both bleeding immensely. There was interference by "Rowdy" Roddy Piper, you'll never guess what happens in this match. Announcers got slogged with chairs, leg drops off ladders and many bumps and spots like that. Maybe not the best street fight but you had two people who are about 50 and they did very well in my books. My rating 8.14/10.Match Eight-The Rock Vs Stone Cold Steve Austin-This is the final encounter between these two. It was their third match at Wrestlemania with their previous encounters at Wrestlemania 15 and 17 with Austin winning on both occasions. This was the second best out of them as Wrestlemania 17 was a really exceptional match. Austin didn't look there mentally or physically but he still put on an exceptional match. There was lots of mocking each other, working each other down, finisher attempts and many more things in this jamp packed match. Will Austin make it 3 for 3 against Rock at Wrestlemania or will Rock finally beat Austin 1,2,3 at Wrestlemania? My rating 8.75/10.Match Nine-Main Event-WWE Championship-Kurt Angle(C)Vs Brock Lesnar-This was an exceptional way to end the show with this match. Two amature wrestlers going at it for the biggest title on the biggest stage of them all. There were many finishers used and countered including an amazing Shooting Star Press by Brock Lesnar. Will that be enough to capture the gold in this excellent match or will Angle prevail with his title. My rating 8.69/10.Overall I believe this show was very good with lots of great matches on the card. Lets see how the marks go. The marks it got are 72.91/90 which is a very good score. Now when we get the percentage for this it is 81.01% which is a great mark. It is equivalent to an A-. This show was an excellent show with all the matches being very good. It also has really good extras. I believe this is a must have for your DVD collection.

reviewText: This is w/o a shadow of a doubt The Best Wrestlemania EVER! of All Time.I mean you had 54,097 fans @ Safeco Field in Seattle, WA, you had 9 Matches @ WM, you had Limp Bizkit, and The Miller Lite Catfight Girls, I mean this is as good as it gets.Matt Hardy vs. Rey Mysterio WWE Cruiserweight Championship-Good Match, but Matt Hardy uses the ropes to gain the Pinfall which was bad, but still a great match and a great way to start WMXIX.Taker vs. A-Train & Big Show w/Limp Bizkit performing Rollin'-awesome Match and Taker's suppose to be Tag Partner Nathan Jones comes out and does a spinning heel kick on Big Show WOW! What IMPACT, and Taker 11-0 @ Wrestlemania.Trish vs. Victoria vs. Jazz Triple Threat Match for the WWE Women's World Championship-awesome Women's Match and The Best Women's Match @ Mania, Steven Richards even hit himself w/The Steel Chair and then gets The Stratusfaction, Trish wins the Gold for a 4th Time, and she looked Sexy Smooth in her Silver Ring Attire, and I don't care what anyone says, this is THE best Women's Title Macth in Wrestlemania History, bar none.Benoit/Rhyno vs. Team Angle vs. Los Guerreros Triple Threat Match for SD! WWE Tag Team Championship-This match was awesome, and it comes to show you that Team Angle does NOT stink! A great win for them in their Wrestlemania debut.HBK vs. Y2J-A great match and this was INDEED a classic.Stacy, Torrie, & The Miller Light Catfight Girls-Comedy, Humorous, but it was great that they put The Coach in his place.Triple H vs. Booker T. Big Gold World Heavyweight Championship-A great match Booker T. giving everything he's got, but Triple H retains the World Title, I feel bad for Booker T. he deserves to be the World Heavyweight Champion again.Hulk Hogan vs. Vince McMahon Street Fight 20 years in the making-AWESOME Match, Piper makes a shocking appearance, Hogan gets revenge on Sylvan Grenier and Hogan wins w/3 Leg Drops, I'm glad that Hogan put Vinnie Mac in his place.The Rock vs. Stone Cold One Epic Encounter-Awesome Match, Rock wins w/3 Rock Bottoms, but Rock and Austin gets an ovation from the fans, excellent job by Rock and Austin.Kurt Angle vs. Brock Lesnar WWE Championship-The Best WWE World Title Match since Hulk Hogan & the late great Andre the Giant from Wrestlemania III, both men w/Amatuer Background, but Lesnar wins the Championship for the 2nd time, and the best part was seeing tremendous sportsmanship from both men, of course Angle suffered a neck injury and Brock a concussion, but Thank God that they're OK.Also the extras were good and excellent, all w/the exception of the Wrestlemania 3rd Degree especially when Triple H trying to intimidate my man Michael Cole, also there are Wrestlemania XIX Press Conferences from Seattle, WA & NYC, there's even Edge in Seattle, Trish Stratus @ the Fan Axcess Tour, Sunday Night Heat Match and clip, 5 Post Match Interviews w/Victoria, Rey Mysterio, A-Train, Nathan Jones, and Torrie Wilson & buddy Stacy Keibler all conducted by Josh Mathews, and check out the Victoria interview, it is funny and it was so sweet that she asked Josh for a hug, also there are 10 Wrestlemania Retro Moments from the WWE Wrestlers, plus Wrestlemania Features, comments on the Hogan/McMahon Match-20 years in the making from future WWE Hall of Famers Mean Gene Okerlund and Bobby "The Brain" Heenan, plus Wrestlemania Promotional Spot, Promos of The Miller Light Catfight Girls, Mr. McMahon Training Vignettes, plus Goldberg WWE Debut on the night after Wrestlemania.Plus there's a Hidden Extra-The Rock and Austin @ the Fan Axcess Tour just talking and being humorous which was cool, BTW.But like I said this 2-Disc DVD is definately a Must Have for every Wrestlemania Fanatic, if you think 21 & 22 was something, well I got news for you this is BETTER than WM21 & 22 and this is the best, Wrestlemania XIX and 2002 Survivor Series are truly Must Have DVD's from WWE Home Video.Also the Women's Title Match is much better than some STUPID Pillow Fight and Evening Gown Match.
summary: Wrestlemania XIX: The Best Wrestlemania of All Time

reviewText: Wrestlemania 19 was one of the much better Wrestlemania's from #10 on. After all, it did have the last time The Rock and Stone Cold Steve Austin would wrestle as active wrestlers, not to mention Hulk Hogan and Mr. McMahon fighting it out in a street fight.But besides that you had lots of great matches before and after them. Top this DVD off with an abundance of great extras, and you would be missing something great if you did not have this DVD.Crusierweight ChampionshipRey Mysterio vs. Matt Hardy [Champion]Nice way to start off WM with high flying moves from Rey and Hardy. I remember this rivalry so well, and this was a great match up between these two. Shannon Moore helped Matt gain the upperhand in some spots, but it was Hardy himself who wins. [By hanging on the ropes I might add] 8/10Handicap MatchBig Show and A-Train vs. The UndertakerI remember this match as well. Both Show and Train combined was almost a thousand pounds. Add Taker, who is a good 300 pounder, and thats a lot of weight in the ring. It actually is good, all three men looked good and looked like they were actually trying to put on a show, but definately not one of Taker's best wins. [You knew he would win against these two]Nathan Jones, once a "student" of the Undertaker, comes down to the ring and levels Big Show. Taker then gives the tombstone to Train to win. Taker extends his win to 11-0  8/10Women's ChampionshipTriple ThreatJazz, vs. Trish vs. victoria [champion]This was back when the women's division had more women who could actually wrestle than these new ladies who just prance around backstage. This was one of the best women's matches in 2003 [There were a lot of them in that year]Victoria was good at doing her psycho impression. Jazz and Trish took some serious bumps in this one. and Trish wins to become a four time women's champion. [i think] 7.5/10WWE Tag Team ChampionshipsTriple ThreatLos Guerreroes vs. Team Angle [Champions] Vs. Rhyno and Chris Benoit.I loved the Guerreroes and Team Angle feud. Add two other great guys in a tag team, and you have a fast paced tag team match, which it was. All six men flew over the ring in fast paced action. Benoit gave some really loud chops in this one, just listen and see what I mean.Team Angle wins after Rhyno gores the hell out of Chavo and then Eddie pulls him out of the ring. Shelton Benjamin grabs the win. Fast paced near the end so don't blink. 8.5/10Shawn Michales vs. Chris JerichoSecond best match of that year. [The first was Angle and Benoit at Royal Rumble.] The two men worked so well together. Lots of chain wrestling and submission moves. The crowd was so into this match, this was the first of four great matches that night.Shawn came back to his first WM after five years and won. After the match Chris Jericho hugs Shawn, then gives him a low blow. Great match besides the post ending. 10/10World Heavyweight ChampionshipBooker T vs. HHH [Champion]This was the first of the four main events and in my opinion it was the worst. Not that the two men suck, they don't, it's just Flair shouldn't have been at ringside to screw with Booker, and the King's commentary isn't the best to try and get used to.Besides that there were some good moments, and both Booker T and HHH did their best. HHH wins, and it would be the last time, so far, where he would win at a WM event. [Just look at WM 20 and 21]Street FightHulk Hogan vs. Mr. McMahonI admit it, I thought this was a good match. A ladder was used, chairs were used, lead pipes and announce tables were broken and destroyed. Plus a very surprise visit by "Hotrod" Rowdy Roddy Piper. The crowd was so into Hogan winning it was unbelievable.If you look at the crowd they go nuts when Piper appears, and when Shane McMahon comes to the ring it got very interesting to try and predict what would happen next. Good match. 9/10The Rock vs. Stone Cold Steve AustinThe Rock said that it was the third match between him and Austin that people would remember the most. I don't agree or disagree about that. While his match at WM 19 was awsome, I did like his last two at WM 17 and 15. But anyways this was a great match to watch.The Rock even goes as far as putting on Stone Cold's vest and actually tries to wear it. Some hard hitting action and funny moments by the Rock made this the second best match of the night. The Rock wins with 3 Rock Bottoms and claims he's done it all in the WWE, that is, until Goldberg arrived the next day. 9.5/10WWE ChampionshipBrock Lesnar vs. Kurt Angle [Champion]Technical wrestling at its best. Both guys are great in this one. I was surprised to see this was the main event, but I quickly got into the match. The most memorable moment was definately Lesnar's shooting star press that backfired completely. Lesnar landed right on his head and damn near broke his neck.Speaking of broken necks, Kurt wasn't so lucky and broke his neck during the match. He continued to figh on, but unfortunately fell to Lesnar's F5. Lesnar wins to his second championship reign. 9/10The extras are so long on this DVD it is almost worth it by themselves. There's too much to name but some are....Goldberg's debut the very next night during Rock appreciation night.Several superstars; like RVD and the dudley boyz looking back at their favorite moments at WM.A special look at Hulk Hogan vs. Andre the Giant at WM 3Several clips of Mr. McMahon training for his match. Its impressive a guy his age is in so good condition.This is definately worth it, I personally think its in the top five WM's of all time.
summary: Safeco Field was never the same again.......

reviewText: A great wrestlemania and ranks up in the top wrestlemanias of all time. Here is a list of the matches:1)Cruiserweight ChampionshipMysterio vs Hardy(C)A great high flying match by both of these men. Trish as the victor. 5/104)WWE tag team championshipsTeam Angle vs Los Guerrero's vs Chris Benoit and RhynoA great tag team match up. Benoit and Guerrero really show their stuff, and prove why they were victorious at wrestlemania 20. Team Angle won with some sneaky tactics. 8.5/105)Shawn Michaels vs Chris "Y2J" JerichoAn amazing contest by two of the greatest in the business. Jericho shows why he was the first undisputed champion, and Shawn Micheals showed why he is the showstoppa.I predicted HBK to win because this was his first wrestlemania in 5 years.An amazing match between these two and one of the greatest matches ever in my book. 10/106)World Heavyweight ChampionshipHHH vs Booker TBooker T is an incredible athlete with a good chance of becoming the champion soon. I give this a 7.5/107) Street FightHogan vs McmahonNot a very good wrestling match but very entertaining match. This match had probably one of the best background stories I have ever seen. I give this a 5/108)Stone Cold vs The RockA great match up by these two. This was the last match Stone Cold was ever in.The Rock was phenomenol in this match up delivering 3 ROCK BOTTOMS to Stone Cold. Austin showed alot of heart and kicked out of 2 rock bottoms before toppiling to the third. 10/109)WWE ChampionshipKurt Angle vs Brock LesnarKurt Angle is the only olympic gold medalist ever, Brock Lesnar is a two time national champion.When you add these things together you get a wrestlemania main event. These two men show why they are so dominant in the wrestling circles. Brock Lesnar gave it his all in this match trying a shooting star press, almost unheard of by a near three hundred pounder. An awesome main event, and incredible effort by both of these men. 10/10A great wrestlemania and it was an incredible card.

reviewText: Looking back on it, Wrestlemania XIX was a fairly anticipated show @ the time. A the time, almost 4 months into 2003, Brock Lesnar won the Royal Rumble, Kurt Angle & HHH were champions, Hulk Hogan, The Rock, and Steve Austin (among others) were set to return, Shawn Michaels making his return to Wrestlemania,  Goldberg was going to make his long awaited WWE debut. All things considered, this had the makings to be a blockbuster show.Here's my review:March 30, 2003; Safeco Field; Seattle, WA1. WWE Cruiserweight champion Matt Hardy vs. Rey Mysterio, (A criminally short match between these two. If given more time, this could've been classic, but it's an above average match to say the least.)**1/22. The Undertaker vs. The Big Show & A-Train in a handicap match,(Originally, Nathan Jones was going to team with the Undertaker, but he was "taken out of action" during the Heat episode before this show. Undertaker defeated Show and A-Train in this match. Not that watchable.)*3. WWE Women's champion Victoria vs. Trish Stratus vs. Jazz in a triple threat match, (Another fairly average match for the women's division.)**4. WWE tag team champions Shelton Benjamin & Charlie Haas vs. Chris Benoit & Rhyno vs. Eddie & Chavo Guerrero in a triple threat match, (Not a bad match @ all. These teams could've had a much better match, but with the next set of matches, we could see that more time was given to the main matches.)**1/25. Shawn Michaels vs. Chris Jericho, (HBK made his grand return to Wrestlemania in this classic match. I enjoy this one every time I watch it.)****1/46. World champion Triple H vs. Booker T, (Myself and others thought that Booker T was going to leave as champion, but HHH ended up winning in the end. Not a bad match per se, barely good, but not great.)**1/27. Hulk Hogan vs. Vince McMahon in a street fight, (Wow, when you have TWO legendary senior citizens competing, can you have a decent match? In the case of these two, you can. Even though it was overbooked, it still was a decent match considering the people involved.)**1/28. The Rock vs. Steve Austin  (After viewing this match on many occasions, it deserves four stars. Both men truly worked in this one, with Rock FINALLY defeating Austin @ Wrestlemania. Not better than the Wrestlemania X-Seven match, but 50% better than the Wrestlemania XV match.)****9. WWE champion Kurt Angle vs. Brock Lesnar, (Two decorated athletes putting on a wrestling clinic in the main event. Everyone knew this was going to be Angle's last match for a while because he had to have neck surgery, other than that, this was a fantastic match.)****1/4Extra Features as wellAlternate Spanish CommentaryWrestlemania 3rd DegreeThe Road to Wrestlemania:Wrestlemania Press Conference in Seatle (September 24, 2002)Edge's Wrestlemania Media TourWrestlamania Press Conference in New York CityWrestlemania Weekend:Trish Stratus - Full AxxessWorld Tag Team Championship from Sunday Night Hear before Wrestlemania: Chief Morley & Lance Storm vs. Rob Van Dam & Kane (*1/2)From Sunday Night Heat: Attack on Nathan JonesPost-Match Commnets: Victoria, Rey Mysterio, A-Train, Nathan Jones, Stacy Keibler & Torrie WilsonWrestlemania Retro - Superstars reveal their favorita 'Mania moment: Christian, D-Von Dudley, Rob Van Dam, Shawn Michaels, Big Show, Spikey Dudley, Bubba Ray Dudley, Diamond Dallas Page, Trish Stratus and Steve AustinWrestlemania Feature:Wrestlemania 1: The BeginningWrestlemania Celebrity Celebrity MomentsHulk Hogan vs. Andre the GiantHulk Hogan at WrestlemaniaUndertaker UndefeatedComments on Hogan vs. McMahon - 20 Years in the Making: Gene Okerland and Bobby HeenanWrestlemania Promotional Spots: Wrestlemania Image Spot, Wrestlemania - 4 Main EventsThe Catfight Girls: Lunch, The Pool, The Rock vs. AustinMr. McMahon Training Vignettes: At Trax Training Center, In the Weight RoomThe Night after Wrestlemania XIX: Goldberg Debuts on Raw (March 31, 2003)Easter EggGo to the "Chapters" section on disc 2 and highlight "The Rock vs. Stone Cold Steve Austin" match and press the right arrow on your remote control. It will take you to a six-minute segment with The Rock interrupting Steve Austin's autograph session at the Fax Axxess party in Seattle.Overall, this was a great show, the best WWE show in the year 2003. Recommended.
summary: Wrestlemania XIX fires on all cylinders!!!!!!!!!
